title: Cute, comfy, stay on well
text: So far (after excitedly trying all of them on right after each other) I really like these headbands! The colors and patterns are so cute. The striped ones are a silkier fabric while the floral printed ones are a more textured fabric. These don't stretch all the way around your head like many headbands do, you have to stretch it over your head around where you want it to be and then style your hair from there. Not the best pick for a quick hair fix, perhaps a standard elastic headband would be best for that! They seem to be pretty sturdy on the head; a lot of headbands can tend to slip around or even fall off. I didn't wear these for a long time, but I tested their strength by moving my head around and they stayed pretty much in place. They are a tad bit more narrow than I had anticipated, but you can sort of splat out the fabric if you like a wider headband like me. I attached a few of the pictures I took while trying them out. I love how they look with my hair both up and down! It adds a touch of flair and class to even a simple bun. Overall I really like these. They fit the style I was looking for with a great price. Definitely recommend!

My husband was an acne sufferer before I knew him, and still gets some problem areas on his back from sitting and getting all sweaty in his office chair. I thought maybe this would help. His skin does seem to bring out the big guns when it comes to attacking ingrown hairs and any other perceived foreign substance.

And I have to say, upon the two-minute inspection I was allowed, it actually does seem to be helping. Even though it's not like he's using it regularly - actually, he uses it whenever I'm allowed to spray it on him after his shower and before he goes to bed. I'd say I manage to get to him about three times a week. And the impact appears, to me, to be noticeable, and beneficial - there are several problem areas that are now looking quite subdued and normal.

I can only imagine what his overall back might look like, if he would just let me do it twice a day every day.

text: I have thick, long hair that falls close to-= my tail bone.  As my hair has gotten longer, one hair tie isn't enough anymore. I wore my hair in a low bun yesterday using 6 spin pins (I wanted a super tight bun) and it held for 13+ hours.  The pins are easy to screw in and super easy to screw out as well. title: I don't feel like my skin is moisturized enough after putting this on
text:
My face usually gets extra dry and sensitive in the winter, so I was really excited to try this. I've been using this for over a month now, here's what I think:

Pros: it's very gentle. It's almost guaranteed that it won't cause any irritation to your skin.

Cons: unfortunately this didn't improve any of the redness that I had already. I don't feel like my skin is moisturized enough after putting this on. My foundation looked pretty flaky on my cheeks at times. During my period when my skin was extra sensitive, it didn't help with my skin any more than the other moisturizers that I've tried.

In conclusion, if your skin is sensitive but in a stable condition, this could be a nice fit for you. For me, it just didn't do enough for the price.

title: Good Quality; Good Variety; Neutral Smell
text:
First, the cosmetics are contained in a small, sturdy, attractive case. You can travel with this kit without being concerned that anything inside will be damaged, and it will not take up much space in your suitcase. (Approx. 7.5"x5.25"x1") The fact that the kit includes cosmetics for the eyes, cheeks and lips enhances its value as a travel kit. One kit does it all, so to speak.

The mirror is rather small, but is workable when you're traveling and don't have a better option.

The testing was done by a woman who was very pleased with this kit. She said she liked it very much, and that it was better than she expected.

Especially important to her was that the "smell" is neutral, without the odor she objected to in some other cosmetics that she has used. She was also quite pleased with the variety and attractiveness of the colors and said the pigment is of good quality.

The small brushes included with the kit are rather flimsy. They may suffice for short trips, but most women are likely to prefer using other brushes when they can.

I considered giving the kit 4 stars because of the brushes, but decided it would not be fair to expect high quality brushes also be included in a kit with such a wide variety of good quality cosmetics, considering the price charged for the kit at the time this review is written.

I was sent this kit for purposes of a review

title: Fresh as a daisy
text:
I normally get the normal Salux from my local Asian grocery, pharmacy, or beauty store. I often get compliments on my soft skin, which I attribute to using this to exfoliate and moisturizing immediately after a shower, but before toweling off. The Salux design works really well to get hard to reach spots like your back and the bottoms of your feet. I've tried off brand towel washcloths and loofah fibers were way too soft. It was time to replace my regular Salux, but after recently moving, it wasn't a priority to get a new one, and was without for a couple weeks.

I don't really get body acne, but I felt crusty and clogged for going a couple of weeks without exfoliating! I could feel hair conditioner on my back not fully rinsed away, even though I showered every day.After getting settled in to my new place, I had finally had it and placed an order for this "hard"(lol) version. The tasteful grey color actually matched the color scheme of my new bathroom. The first shower that I took once I received this was so refreshing! I felt like a snake shedding its skin, like a Phoenix reborn in cleansing fire. It was the satisfaction of scratching an itch except the itch is on your entire body. I love the feeling of a brand new Salux! Hopefully the "hard" version sustains that feeling for longer. It's holy grail right now, until I can find something that's as effective but zero waste. On that note, a Salux is more hygienic and sustainable than a regular loofah because the knotted fibers of a loofah don't dry completely and are therefore more susceptible to bacteria and mildeww growth.

title: A versatile oil that is top quality.

It made my hair super soft! I don't recommend using this oil without the dropper though, it's way too runny and pours out quickly. The smell lingers a long time, but the oil has a nice fragrance to it. I really enjoyed trying out this oil complimentary of New York Biology for testing purposes. title: AMAZING PRODUCT but scent too strong and only found in small bottle
text:
I have thick curly coily AA hair.

It smells a tad too strong and perfumy, and does remind me of waterfalls and springs. It is thicker and creamier than other Suave naturals. It provides great slip, makes my hair soft and fluffy hours after drying, and my hair curls instantly, which lets me know my hair is moisturized.

Waterfall Mist is a great conditioner but not the best Suave bargain. You can find it in stores for as low as $0.85-$1, but it's only available in 12 ounces, whereas Suave Coconut is $1.50 for 33 ounces. So in the long run, this particular scent is not the best purchase for your money. My favorite Suave is Everlasting Sunshine and Coconut, which work even more amazingly on my hair but come in larger sizing with more pleasant scents. For this reason I would not repurchase this particular scent again even though I had a great experience with it. If you don't mind paying the same price for less product and really like the scent, then this is a great buy for you.

It's a great daily moisturizer, but it doesn't have sunscreen in it. I'm trying to streamline my morning routine, so adding a separate sunscreen step is a hassle. However, since my skin is actually looking better, I'll try not to complain about it too much.

The cream is thick, but it absorbs quickly and leaves my skin feeling soft.

The best part really is seeing the redness disappear from my skin. The cream is expensive, but it's worth the price when you can actually see the results.

title: I wanted to try it because I have terrible ingrown hair everywhere on my legs (I wax)
text:
The Brush: This is a new method for me. And I've only used the brush a couple times (just received it 3 days ago). I wanted to try it because I have terrible ingrown hair everywhere on my legs (I wax), cellulite plus skins a little loose on my tummy (3 kids)... So my ideas for this were exfoliation, reduce cellulite appearance and tighten skin. So far, I have noticed how it's easier to see the hairs stuck under the surface which means it is doing a good job already exfoliating. I also notice my skin looks less bumpy and more fresh. My goal is to use it 3x/week. I will return in a few weeks with updated results.

The Oil: What a heavenly scent... I'm using it on my neck down to my toes and the feeling of my skin - looks and feels, smooth, silky, succulent (can I say that?) Plus, the scent is light enough you could add perfume if desired; i usually do when I get to work a couple hours later and don't even smell the oil by then. I LOVE this oil! Would never have tried it but received it as a gift with purchase with my brush and I just want to THANK YOU!!!!

My Conclusion: ORDER IT! Totally worth it.

title: A Must Have, REALLY!  Buy It!!!
text:
Just so you know, I have seen the original version of this glove for awhile & have been extremely skeptical about how useful it could be. It looked silly to me even with one thumb, LOL! However, I am coming off of two arm and hand surgeries back to back (right & left ) & all my brushes were extremely dirty and I was dreading washing them like the plague. (I'm still recovering so my hands & arms are only at 80% strength) I ran across this new version & watched the video on Sigma's site and thought I would try it out because I really needed something to make this easier right now.

I have many brushes including a bunch of big dense ones like the SigMax brushes. I loath the chore of washing my brushes. I do it less often than I should. My hands become prunes, I wreck my nails and it takes for-like-ever! Plus, I can never seem to get the big dense ones clean enough deep in the center no matter how long I stand there and try to wash them.

Today I used this brush cleaning glove and HOLY FRIGGIN' MOLY!!! It's next level stuff!

It was so EASY to DEEPLY clean all my brushes in a FRACTION of my normal time. My dense brushes have never been this clean. It was an actual pleasure to wash them! Never thought I would ever say that.

Do not get an imitation. I saw those & thought about saving some money but in the end bought this glove. They really designed this to actually do all the work for you AND save your hands & nails. It is well thought out.

All the different areas have a very useful purpose that do all the work. You need all the different areas. The area where you shape your brush at the end actually also squeezes out all the excess water from even those dense SigMax brushes. They felt 50% dry right after washing! I'm sure they will dry faster than ever. The terry inner glove made the whole silicone glove experience really nice and cozy. Your hand is comfortable all during the washing & after. None of that sweaty, sticky feeling you can get with rubber gloves. My hand was completely dry even after about 30 brushes!

I like this new design, with the 2 thumbs, because you can always use your dominant hand to hold the brush. With one thumb you would have to switch hands to use the other side of the glove. One side is for face/larger brushes & the other is for eye/smaller brushes.

I use Dr. Bronner's Castile Liquid Soap in the Baby Mild formula. Get yourself a pump dispenser & mix half soap and half water in the dispenser. Having the pump helps speed along the washing process as you just pump the soap onto the center cleaning area of the glove. You never have to put down the brush you are cleaning. This also helps keep the brush aimed down helping you not get water running up into the ferrule by accident as you work.

This glove also makes it easy to know, just by sight, when your brush is completely clean, soap foam is white, and completely rinsed, no foam comes out of your brush when swirled after rinsing.

My brushes are thoroughly deep cleaned for the first time in ages. They look brand new!

If you have a bunch of brushes or even if you don't have that many but have some of the big dense ones, think of this glove as an investment. It will help you preserve the life of your brushes and keep bacteria off your face, yuck.

It is really well made and should last a really long time. They only thing I could see happening is replacing the inner glove as it is terry cloth.

I LOVE this and will happily be washing my brushes all the time now. My face, hands & nails are all going to benefit.

title: Great price on Amazon
text:
I found this on Amazon for about $5 cheaper than any of my local stores. I also have the Fusion Power so I got this as my travel razor. Well, turns out I like this much better than my Fusion Power and it is now my everyday razor!

One small complaint is the case, or lack thereof, that this comes with. There is a small plastic holder that covers just the blades themselves and a small part of the razor. Very minimalist which is fine if that's what you want. I would prefer something a little larger but not enough to take off any stars.

Pair this razor with the Cremo shaving cream (http://www.amazon.com/Cremo-Cream-Shave-177/dp/B001KYVZPY/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1358801609&sr=8-1&keywords=cremo) and you will have yourself a buttery smooth face everyday.

A note on Gillette customer service, it is great. My Fusion Power broke, out of the blue, and I emailed them to express my displeasure as a longtime Gillette user. They answered my email and mailed me a coupon for a free Fusion Power to replace my broken one! That is how you keep your customers happy.

title: Im in LOVE with my mirror!! üòç
text: Ive been wanting one of these mirrors for a while now. And im SO happy i finally found the Perfect one. Its light weight, and sleek looking. Everyone thinks i spent $100 or more on it! It has a good sturdy base. It was easy to put together. Just snap the base onto the neck of the mirror and your good to go. Came charged. The light has three levels of brightness. And the button to turn the light on and up, is conveniently placed on the back of the mirror towards the bottom. Its great placement in that it allows you to turn it on and adjust the lighting and angle with one hand, and without having to put your fingers on the mirror, leaving finger prints. The light that it puts off it amazinnng. Makes my skin look smoother then it really is! So its like having a filter on if you take a selfie in it. Not to mention the ring light makes your eyes look beautiful and doesnt leave shadows on your face so it helps with symmetrical application or plucking. No unblended foundation ever again with this mirror! üòÅüòÅ  I included a picture of my reflection, AFTER i peeled off the protective film that comes on the mirror with "AMIRO" written on it... to try and show just how crystal clear the mirror really is. It doesnt distort your reflection at all. Which is a huge plus,because many other similar products do. The charging cord is well made, you charge for an hour and it lasts an entire day! (Youd never need it to be on for 24s hours, so basically u charge it once, and it will last you well over a week before youd need to charge it again) ive had mine for about a week and a half and havnt had to charge it ever. Except just to try it n make sure everything worked. Ive used it every morning (about 15 mins) and at night (another 10/15 mins) plus at random times. So deff good battery life. It shipped and arrived fast. Seller was polite, quick to respond and helpful when answering my pre purchase questions as well. Im so happy i finally have one of these mirrors i see everywhere. And that i snagged it for a good price and it exceeded my expectations. Id give this product two thumbs up. Lol It would work perfect for both professionals and novices.

title: great shaving experience
text: Braun 7-790cc: Very gentle, fast, and close shave. Compared with my old shaver (Philishave HQ7415) 10x less skin irritation and 3x faster. 5 stars for the shave. Positive surprise: You can charge the shaver without the cleaning station, only with the cord, and also use it with the cord when it is not charged. Disadvantages: a) Cleaning with tap water is clearly more tedious than for simpler shavers (like my old Philips). b) Doesn't bother me, might bother others: It is louder than other shavers. c) "Hidden" costs: 5 USD/month for the cleaning cardridges and from the 19th month of use on additional 2 USD/month for the replacement shaving unit when everything is used as recommended. But compare the high cost for Gilette Sensor blades plus foam! d) Pure cosmetics (but if you buy the Mercedes you want perfect design): The lowest bar indicating battery charge has a red frame, so red = bad. At the same time, the best bar for hygiene status has a red frame as well, so here red = optimum. Doesn't make sense. In addition the green LEDs on the cleaning station have some cross-talk. If one is on, you can think two are on, at least in a dark bathroom as some light is bleeding through...

title: It works !
text:
Since using the goodnight magnesium lotion I haven‚Äôt had trouble falling asleep, staying asleep, and I have experienced a deeper sleep. I usually struggled to get to bed by 10 p.m, and would end up staying up until 12-2 a.m. I apply the lotion to the bottoms of my feet since the feet and spine have the largest pores and receptors in the body. I also apply on my stomach rubbing where my belly button is for faster absorption. I have my 10 and 12 year old sons apply to the bottoms of their feet as well .

Highly recommend for everyone including postpartum Moms who are waking up frequently. Apply in between feedings, when baby is up so you are able to experience a deeper sleep while baby sleeps. If you have little ones - apply to the bottoms of their feet and put on some socks. It‚Äôs that simple . Blown away by how efficient this product is.

title: Much Room for Improvement
text:
I didn't buy from this Amazon vendor and am still in the installation process. This is what I feel about this product so far:
1) The funtions and the price seems very attactive. However, there are many design issue made the installation process not pleasant.
2) The installation manual, as expected through preview, is horrible. There are many key steps not clearly stated. I have to figured them out myself and it took me long time to do so.
3) The design is not space saving. The hardwares are behind the glass panels which demand space. Although it claims to be standard 60X32. The space inside the enclosure is much smaller than that because of the hardware behind the glass panels. This, by the way, is not clearly explained, and I concerned about not having enough bathroom space to host it. I had to put the frame up to understand that it requires 60X32 finished space to host the unit. Essentially treat it like a washer/dryer.
4) The drainage design is not American standard, and I was told it's European. The drainage pipe is only 1 1/2" (American uses 2" pipe) and no clear instruction in the menu on drainage hookup or choices of rough in preparation. The flexible drainage pipe looks cheap and I am not sure how long it will last before leaking.

I'll update you once the unit is finished and tested. Oeverall, the price seems really attractive. I recommend to have an experienced guy, which is hard to find, to put it together.

The contractor just got the installation 95% done. The unit looks beautiful. Everything works. I didn't regret the purchase, and feel the manufacturer should improve the product, especially installation manual, to deserve more stars.

title: Looks delicious and smells great!
text:
After years of mistreating my hair with hair color products and a bleaching mishap a month ago, I was looking for something to re-fortify my hair while conditioning and giving me extra moisture. So I bought the Hairgurt Intense Repair Deep Conditioner in Almond honey. Let me just tell you that it really does look edible!! And it smells edible! It's not a strong smell and it leaves no trace of scent afterwards. The texture is also that of food--it looks and feels like whipped butter.
But we don't buy this to eat it so how did my hair do? My hair did very well but not better than with other less costly products. That is why this gets 4 stars instead of 5. My hair is normally wavy but is not coarse. Due to hair coloring as I mentioned, it had taken a beating and my wave actually diminished but my hair became coarser and very frizzy. After using this hairgurt the first day, my hair did feel smooth afterward for the rest of the day. It dried a bit frizzy but not much. I do not blow dry my hair. However, after going to bed at night, sleeping on cotton pillowcase, my hair was super coarse and frizzy the next day. I did not give up. I used the treatment for 3 more days but always with the same result. I've had better results with other treatments I bought at a local beauty supply store. However the hairgurt DOES work, if only for the day. Maybe it will be better with continued use and if I continue and get better results, I will then update my review.
Please ask any questions and I will do my best to answer. Thank you.

title: Works great, strong scent
text:
Have been using this bar for over a month now. I have fine, thinish hair. We have a whole house water softener system, otherwise we would have very hard water. Now with that out of the way, I love how the bar lathers up and cleans my hair. No residue and no need for a conditioner after. I rub the bar on my hands rather than directly onto my head, making sure I have lots of water in my hair so that the lather is evenly distributed throughout my hair. This method works very well for me. It rinses clean and leaves my hair feeling soft.
The only downside for me is the intensity of the scent. It is much too strong even though the site shows it to be low intensity.
My bar sits on a wire shelf at the back of my shower so it does dry out between uses; have not had it get mushy. I wash my hair every other day and my bar hardly shows any use so it should last quite some time.

title: I love everything about conditioners and what it can do for ...
text:
I love everything about conditioners and what it can do for your hair. So when I saw this was available at a discount for review, I decided to try it out. This came in two short days with no shipping issues. When I received it, I couldn't believe how incredibly large the jar is. It's huge! The first time I used it I could see how hydrating it was to my dried out split ends (which I need to get trimmed off). I like to mix fractionated coconut oil with this treatment cream. Natural coconut oil contains fatty acids that help to immerse each hair follicle with beneficial vitamins and minerals. When the oil is used with a scalp massage, the lauric acid in the oil help to shield the scalp from lice and dandruff which can inhibit hair growth and affect hair health.

Using coconut oil for hair is one of the most natural ways to increase moisture in the hair shaft. When the hair is dry, the shaft becomes frayed and is easily damaged. Not only does this affect the health of the hair, but it also causes the hair to look frizzy, dried out and damaged.

Those who use coconut oil for hair mask treatments find the fatty acids are able to bind with the proteins in their hair so the hair is sealed with protection, trapping in the moisture and making the hair soft, silky and shiny. This works out for me because I get Brazilian Blowouts on my hair and have plenty of proteins for it to bind to.

I couldn't quite tell what the ingredients are exactly in this as I don't recognize them as being something "whole" or natural. That worries me a bit, but it does work great when I mix it with my coconut oil and it keeps my hair soft and smooth without being weighed down.

applying lashes before actually trying it on a person.
We like it came with the tweezers, rings, brushes,

using the glue. We found the rings open in the back for bigger fingers.
We found the tweezers to work well and pick up the lashes gently.
We found the flat mannequin head with replaceable
eyes to work well for our practice. It is heavier built and
should last. It also has a place in the back for those who
have the stand. We do not. All eyes have lashes on them already
just like real eyes. The trick is to learn to put these on well
enough that they also look like real lashes and blend in with the
natural lashes. This is where our practice part comes in.
We like it came with the flat head and 3 extra replaceable sets of eyes
in case there is a mess up learning how to apply and remove
the lashes. There is 2 of us trying to learn.
There was enough supplies in the box for both of us. There is also
5 sheets of 7 pairs of isolation papers.
We did find the glue was in a tiny bottle only 5 ml. Since we use
only a pin head dot to apply the lashes it might last.
We like that everything works well for the training of applying
lashes.
We like there is different sized lash extensions for our
practice and there is plenty to practice with.
We found this a good learning tool and easy to use.
I have enclosed pictures so you can make a informed
decision based on your own personal needs.
Yes I would recommend this product.

title: Lavendar scent not strong enough to control odors
text: First off, I live in the south.....the deep, crazy hot, muggy south. I NEED deoderant down here if I want people to talk to me. I've tried several natural deodorants, plain coconut oil, the clear deoderants that are available at healthfood stores, the crystal.....they just don't hold up down here. Pit paste held up a bit better than the other stuff. I tried the lavendar scent. It's okay....smells kind of like laundry detergent. It does not keep me smelling good for longer than half a day. And something in it makes my skin burn after using it for a week. I watched a video wear this girl rubbed a lime on her armpit to get rid of odors, and then I switched to Schmidt's stick deoderant , with bergamot and lime essential oils. The lime one works WAY better at eliminating odors, and the stick kind is easier to apply (it's not nearly as soft, so I'm not over applying). The two brands have pretty much the same ingredients, so I would suggest looking for a citrus scented version if you're concerned with controlling odors.

title: Works well, easy to use, one drawback is tricky to take apart and put back together for cleaning
text:
We purchased Pet Electric Hair Clipper: professional tools for your love pets/grooming clipper, from Caleegi.

Everything appears to be quite well made, of sturdy construction. The scissors and nail trimmers came out of the box sharp, and have a good weight to them. The nail trimmers have a good locking mechanism, metal, not plastic; I think it will last. The set comes with a convenient little storage pouch, which I hadn't noticed on the item description specs list. I like the colors of the pouch. They're cute. The pouch easily fits everything in the kit, except the brush. You can make the brush fit, but I dont think you can make the brush and electric clippers fit. I couldn't. The electric clippers come with a usb powered charger cord, but not a charger block. This is not a standard charger. If you lose this charge cord, you may be hard pressed to find a replacement.

The brush is of good construction, and the ergonomic handle grip is a joy to hold. For real, it just feels good in your hand. I like the push button hair dislodger for easy brush cleaning. Our dog is fairly short haired, straight and wirey, and our cat is fluffy but on the short side of medium length hair. It took very little hair off them, and I haven't found a product better than the Furminator for brushing them. But I've had and worked with longer haired dogs, and for a Great Pyrenees, Burnese Mountain Dog, or Saint Bernard, I think this would be the perfect brush.

The nail file worked great. The comb I intend to keep for myself- it's perfect for my wiry, sometimes wavy, sometimes curly, always disobedient hair.

The electric clipper charged fairly quickly, enough that I could take it for a test spin about 15-20 minutes after plugging it in. I love the electronic digital display, showing how far along in its charging it is, and the RPMs of the clipper blades. I love that it came with a little bottle of lubricant solution for the blades (none of my personal trimmers ever have). The little obligatory cleaning brush to sweep between the blades looks much the same that any electric trimmer does, but I found it shed a wire or two with every pass throughthe blades, which my personal trimmer brushes do not.

I tried the electric clippers out on myself first. I was a little bummed that the nearly universal gaurds that come with clippers designed for people did not fit. The clippers are much more quiet then most clippers, which is good for not startling pets. I used the clippers with the guard on the sides of my head and with no gaurd to shave my face. It went easily through my hair, had no trouble, and gave me a close, even shave. And I went a little rough to see if there was any danger of maybe cutting a squirming or struggling pet, and it seems very safe.

The clipper blades came off pretty easy for cleaning, but were kind of tricky to put back on, and in trying to do so, I hit at a funny angle and the entire clipper assembly fell apart in to 4 pieces. That was annoying, but after messing around with it for about a half hour, I was able to put it back together, and it still worked fine. I would be hesitant to take it apart for cleaning again, though I'm sure I will. Despite this one design flaw, I still think overall this is a pretty quality product.

It comes on extremely cold, too, but don't let that fool you into thinking it can't be massaged into the skin. Thick hair in the way shouldn't cause any problem spreading this around, which is good if you don't all of your facial hair.

The smell is like getting "smacked in the face with a key lime pie," as per most reviews online, but it's really more of a sweet lime with a *touch* of acidity. title: Good Portable ALL in ONE nail clipper / grooming kit

My stepmother gave me a personal grooming kit almost 20 years ago. It did not have all the things this kit had, but nevertheless I still have and treasure that kit as my Stepmom has since passed away. It's something I keep and remember her by.

This kit is like the 3.0 version of what she gave me. It even has some items I'm not sure of the use.

As soon as I opened it, it became useful. Oftentimes I'm sitting at my desk for super long periods of the day and oftentimes I may start biting my nails or even cleaning my ears as I'm looking at my computer screens. This kit allows me to clip my nails without having to run to the bathroom and grab my mother's kit. The tools in this kit allows it to be a one stop shop so that means it has a permanent place near my office desk. You can't go wrong getting this.

Pros
Fairly Compact
Portable
Many tools
Stainless steel
It has the ear scraper / cleaner.. That makes it a winner right there.

Cons
Not really any.. I just wish I knew what all the tools were used for. I guess I have to do some researching.

title: The best electric shaver ever
text:
PROS: close shave; less skin irritation and no cut; quick charging; convenient LED displays

CONS: pricy; pricy cartridges; fragile looking body

I've had this shaver for 10 days and am loving it. It only took me several days to get used to it. It is the closest shave I've ever had with an electric. Blade razors, like Mach 3, give better shaves but they usually leave cuts on my face so this was the best thing. I like the quick 1-hour charge a lot. The shaving time is actually shortened for me because I just do it during the shower. Nevertheless, the shaver at $120 is not cheap. Like others said, Nivea cartridges can run out fast. But I found a remedy- Nivea "after shave balm" 3.3 oz. at $4.79 in a local CVS pharmacy or Walmart gives you the same quality as little five Nivea 0.4 oz. cartridges(total 2 oz.) at $5 do. I hope this helps.

I'm just now learning about the different types of ribbon out there to hold the larger bows more stable. I have not found or purchased a new set, yet. I think if these were longer, it might not have been a complete miss for what I was looking for. The set with the crowns and the ribbon rings as the hooks, do fit over my daughter's dresser draw knobs, which I was hoping, and looking for when ordering. I'm still giving them a 3 star review, because they would be nice for other's needs as I've mentioned. A suggestion would be to make much longer ones. title: A Cheap But Effective Attractant!
text:
I have to say I am pleasantly surprised! This simple little mixture of only 5 bucks is actually effective! I received it yesterday and took it out for a test run today for work. I work in a retail chain store so I communicate with many people every day and I got hit after hit after hit.

My intent in wearing this was to evoke a warm and friendly persona which I radiate naturally but because this is a store, customers can be a tad dismissive to employees. So I applied my Pure Instinct to the sides of my collarbone, behind my ears, the veins on my wrist, and various dabs on my clothes so the smell can last a little longer. What a sweet and pleasant smell it has! It smells a tad like melon and bubble gum. A little powder too. Smells delicious! Despite these sweet scents, it doesn't smell "kiddie" and "immature" and plus the smell is light and could never be overpowering. It's quite the flattering scent that you could wear alone or compliment with your own signature perfume. Also the actual pheremone count in the bottle does seem to be a bit low (which is not a problem) so you cannot overdose on the pheremones and get bad effects. It's waaay too hard to overdose so dab as much as you feel is necessary on yourself. ^^

From the moment my shift started, customers actually stopped and listened when I offered them my help and advice. They would take my bags and even passing customers would come up just to compliment me and tell me kind things. This is definitely a unisex attractant because both genders were equally affected in positive ways and made my job very fruitful today! This is the perfect pheremone mixture to use at work if you're looking for a pheremone for the work place!

Many times customers would pass me by, stop, and exclaim that I smell wonderful and ask what I was wearing. A couple of guys came to me just to talk about how delicious I smelled, haha! Because I was having such great and magnetic success at my job, my managers were constantly praising me with excitement and even the DISTRICT MANAGER who stopped by to check on our store was highly impressed by my energy and how attracted to me the customers were.

The smell does lessen after about 4 hours and I was not able to smell it anymore unless I really sniffed myself but it seems others could still smell it because I was still being complimented on my scent. Not bad! I reapplied on my break just for extra safety though, hehe!

This has been a highly successful test run and I will be wearing this lovely magic in a bottle quite often! <3

title: Doesn't Irritate My Skin

The microbeads have to be crushed or else you have little white beads on your face. It's not difficult to break the beads. I just press on them and they rub into the skin. After applying the serum, my face was really dry. I have been using this at night. I have a multi-step skin care routine so I followed this with my nighttime moisturizer, then retinol, and some face oil. The serum doesn't irritate my sensitive skin. There is a mild scent, but nothing that I could recognize. Overall, it's okay. I haven't noticed any tightening or improvements in my skin. However, as a regular user of anti-aging products, I wasn't expecting anything new.

text:
Quick absorbing, non greasy watery hand & body lotion. I like my body lotions to be on the thin side as I find it easier/quicker to apply as well as quicker to absorb. When I have extra rough spots, then I don't mind using a thicker emollient. But for just out of the shower lotion to lock in moisture.. I want a thinner lotion. This provides that. Yet, it is moisturizing enough to use any other time of day. Leave at kitchen sink for hand moisturizing as needed is great too. But not at bathroom sink lest someone mistakes it for toothpaste, haha. It is in a toothpaste style container. Just flip cap and squeeze.

It feels nice on skin, has no added fragrance. I like their 1513 face lotion and I like this hand/body lotion too. I tend to have dry skin, so I find both are better for me for summer or days I just a light hydration boost. Easy to use, no frills lotion that is gentle on skin. I appreciate the nourishing ingredients and that they offer a no fragrance added option. Any hint of scent is entirely naturally occurring. However, this may not be for you if you seek to avoid essential oils as is is listed at the end.

Overall it is a nice product. No irritation. No issues thus far.

Key Ingredients:
--Rose Flower Water: Helps maintain the skin's pH balance
--Organic White Willow Bark Extract: A natural exfoliant that helps reveal brighter, radiant skin; Acts as an astringent and anti-inflammatory
--Aloe Leaf Juice: Hydrates and helps to lock in healing ingredients ‚Ä¢ Hemp Seed Oil: Treats inflammation and redness

Organic Aloe Leaf Juice, Organic Coconut Oil, Glycerin, Stearic Acid, Emulsifying Wax, Witch Hazel Water, Vitamin E, Sunflower Seed Oil, Phenoxyethanol, Organic Hemp Seed Oil, Rose Flower Water, CBD, Organic White Willow Bark Extract, Organic Rosemary Leaf Extract, Organic Neem Seed Oil, Organic Alcohol, Xanthan Gum, Tetrasodium Glutamate Diacetate, Essential Oil

title: Very good razor for the price
text:
Upgraded to this razor after my old Remington died, and I've been very happy with it. It cut a bit close, which irritated my skin at first, but I think that was just me getting used to the "Lift & cut."

This would be an excellent razor if it wasn't for two features (or lack thereof) that make it a pain to use.

1. The internal battery is NiCd. This type of battery has "memory" to it, which means for optimal performance, the battery should be fully drained before you recharge it. Otherwise, the life of the battery will slowly shorten until the battery is useless.

2. There isn't a low battery indicator.

By itself, either of these features wouldn't pose a problem. Combined, you're left wondering when you'll have to charge the shaver, or when you're off on that business trip, if you'll need to bring the charger.

In the long run, this razor is cheap enough and I expect the battery to last for years. Still, it would have been better if the battery was made of NiMH or some technology that's not 15 years old.

title: Gentle, Soothing Moisture
text:
Being that my facial skin changes greatly during the winter months, I thought this serum might help to re-establish some moisture while battling my winter dryness. This review is for: [SKIN&LAB] Barrierderm Milky Serum | Infused with Milk Ceramide Complex, Squalane, and Panthenol to ...

I have used products from Skin & Lab before and liked most of them, and this serum is no exception. I was coming off of a different moisturizer that really irritated my skin, so I introduced this serum slowly. I started using it only once a day and once that previous irritation cleared up I moved up to twice a day.

This serum is somewhere in between watery and a cream. The glass bottle is opaque and the serum does dispense as milky-looking. It has no scent that I can detect. The dropper dispenses enough for about half my face, so I've been using two droppers per application. It has soothed my skin, clearing up my previous Rosacea break out and smoothing out my skin. I have an oily t-zone and a super dry chin this winter, and all of that seems to be gone now.

Due to these cold, breezy winter months, I have been using a moisturizer over this serum. I suspect that in the summer months, I might not even need to do that.

I'm looking forward to continued use of this product and when it's gone I will most likely buy more. The price is affordable and this works wonderfully on my dry, winter skin.

title: An Incremental Improvement, But Worth It
text: The biggest improvement here is in the handle, which feels better than my old Fusion Power Phantom, though they look pretty much identical side by side.  I've long missed my third-party handle for my Mach 3, and this one still isn't as nice as my original Fusion Manual handle (which was made in eastern Europe), but, like I said, this one seems to be an improvement over the previous Fusion Power, and I've become sold on the vibrating handles.  They're always making tweaks to the blade cartridge, and this one is better, seeming to glide more effortlessly while delivering the same close shave as before.  The warming face wash included would be nice to use if one doesn't shower before shaving, but that's a rarity for me, and the cooling aftershave feels pretty much like every aftershave Gillette has made for about the past 25 years, and they never quite do it for me.  The Fusion Shave Gel is the same as before, though I prefer the moisturizing variety to the sensitive one included here.

title: and so far I am quite pleased in how my skin is responding so far
text:
I am still quite new to using hyaluronic acid serum, and so far I am quite pleased in how my skin is responding so far. This particular serum is thinker than the previous product I tried, and I like this quality much more. It is thinker without being greasy and it soaks in to my skin and feels more moisturizing than the last product I tried. The overall health of my skin is far less dry than it was before I started using hyaluronic acid serum. My skin is smoother and a lot of the dark spots and old acne scars are starting to noticeably fade. Hyaluronic acid serum is now a permanent part of my face care routine and I am glad it is something that my sensitive skin not only tolerates but is showing some great improvements. This is something that I will not be without and will most definitely repurchase when this bottle is empty, and that will be a long time from now given that this a 2 ounce bottle and a little does go a long way.

title: No greasy feel!!
text:
I‚Äôve tried Skederm products and I really like all of them. This one was no exception because I think it works really well. The main purpose is to form a protective barrier to keep moisture locked into the skin to keep it hydrated.

FEEL: It is not greasy, which I am always concerned about when I buy a moisturizer. Instead it feels almost like a satin finish, almost like a primer. It can be worn under makeup as well. It does keep my face moisturized without that greasy, oily feeling and look.

BENEFITS: This is more of a prevention cream than anything to repair. It will help maintain the skin‚Äôs elasticity and prevent wrinkles and sagging. This is because as we age, the skin loses elasticity due to a loss of collagen and moisture. This also has macadamia nut oil for antioxidant purposes, which is so important in a moisturizer. This prevents cellular aging.

MY EXPERIENCE: I have combination skin. It is oily in some areas and dry in others. I put this on the dryer areas to even out my skin, which has worked really well. I leave it off my nose, which tends to get oily. I had very oily skin in my younger years and I think that this would have worked well for that because it is not really a typical moisturizer. It feels very much like a makeup primer.

So I have been trying, since I turned 32, different eye creams and wrinkles treatments. For the cost of some of the professional treatments, I was always disappointed with the results. And then after I had paid triple, what this Cardea Luxe Skin Care product cost, I had to try it .

Just to be clear, this product isn't meant to be your end all solution. I also use, hydraulic acid, rose water toner with No alcohol, and I also use a peptide moisturizer and when I clean my face in use an exfoliant as well. If you need something that will help you over time, have healthier looking eyes and face, this is a good one that I definitely recommend. title: Maybe I'm not the ideal customer? Just not a great experience...
text:
I can honestly say that I've given this thing a try.
I've had it for nearly a month now & have tried all the colors on a regular basis and... the jury is still out here.

Maybe I started too late? Maybe my very dry, very sensitive, sun damaged 60 year old skin is past redemption?
I'm not quite sure, but the improvement is - negligible?? Imperceptible??
I clean my face, wear the mask, moisturize, & wait. A couple times/week for a couple of weeks now.
I think part of my problem is that I don't find the process relaxing. Having lights on my face & having to sit still. My hyper tendencies kick in & I get squirmy and anxious.
I also have a large size head, so the face mask is pretty snug. Rather torturous, actually.

So -- as far as the review goes -- the product is fine. It does as it says it will, apparently. I'm just not the target audience! I'll share it with my smaller headed, more low key sister.

**Thank you for reading this review & I hope that it's Helpful!**

text: I got these as a gift for my 12 year old niece who loves doing nail design. I chose the speckled leopard print set and the design is absolutely adorable. It takes a delicate manner to get these peeled and placed without messing them up or having air bubbles. I have seen both better and worse products which is why this set is getting 3 stars from me. title: High quality
text:
This is a review for: Sand & Sky Face Roller & Massager Tool. Aussie Skincare Essentials Firming Face Roller, Sculpt, Sooth & Contour to Banish Puffiness and Boost Serum Absorption.

This is a nice, very high quality facial roller. It doesn't compare to the usual ones made of plastic.
This has good weight, glides very smoothly and also can be frozen or heated.
It really feels nice on the skin and does a good job massaging. It does a wonderful job massaging in serums and whatnot to promote better absorption as well.

If I'm being nit-picky, the only problem I would have is that due to the angled rollers, going one way vs the other feels different and if you don't rotate the roller, it will give you an uneven massaging experience.
Also, the price point probably would be an issue as you can potentially get a lesser quality roller for way cheaper.

Overall, quite happy with it.

title: THIN and doesn't hold a curl
text:
I ordered the 14/16/18 with the 12 inch closure. Although my stylist did a great job installing the hair and closure, this hair is THINNNN! I posted a photo of what all three bundles look like in a pony tail after being curled 8 hours prior. You may be wondering, what curl? Exactly. The second pic shows how my hair was styled fresh out the chair.
I know others say you may need 4-5 bundles for fullness but my head is not that big for that many layers of tracks! You can typically get the job done with 3 bundles (especially if the hair is under 20"). In regards to the hair quality, we all know this is Chinese hair. It's silky straight that's been steamed to create waves. I don't forsee it getting tangled and the closure is passable. The hair does have a slight red tint to it and you can identify red strands of "hair" throughout all the bundles so at least that's consistent o__o. You get what you pay for. And yes there's a chemical smell.
Would I buy this hair again? NO! Would I install it again? NO

title: I had to try it for myself.
text:
After reading all of the bad reviews on this new Norelco shaver, I swore I was not going to buy this unit.

Well, a few months ago I realized my local stores didn't stock my HQ5 Norelco replacement blades anymore and I about had a heart attack. Oh, darn, I am now being forced to upgrade and I was quite happy with my current shaver.

I have had a Norelco 5885XL for the past 13 years. I love this unit and it suits me well. This only noteworthy things about this old unit is that I have had to have the batteries replaced only two times, but this is normal since they wear out every 6 years or so.

Here is my 1050x review.. it was painful to write, but here goes..

--This is a noisy shaver folks.. I graduated to a 5885XL a long time ago and was surprised of the whisper quiet shave it delivered. The 1050x is about 2-3 time noisier than my 15 year old Norelco, WTH? This is not good. I simply cannot accept a noisy shaver. This thing is inches away from my ears at 5am and that is very annoying. I need peace and quiet at those early hours, and this would not work long term.

--What a bad shave. Starting with a 2-day shadow growth, I shaved half of my face with my trusty 5885XL [using 1.5 year old blades] and the other half with my shiny new 1050x unit. I actually had my wife feel both shaves afterwords to confirm I wasn't being overly critical of my new toy.

As I suspected, she confirmed my 5885xl produced a better shave, in about the same amount of time.

As I shaved with the 1050x, I realized that I was going over the same growth areas without making things smoother, especially around the neck. I was getting tired, frustrated, and irritated. The pivoting head technology is clearly inferior to Norelcos older units.

--Here come the skin irritations: Ahhh!!!
Just a few minutes after my shave test had ended, my 1050x side was now irritated and not feeling comfortable [like my 5885xl side was]. Having used Norelcos all of my shaving life, about 25 years, this irritation I feel is not normal, and I do not find this acceptable; even if there is a break-in period; not for me there isn't. no thanks..

--Bad charging system! What the heck is it with this terrible charging system. I should be able to plug the unit in directly and not have to lug around more junk to lose or break while on travel. The AC adapter cable does not even fit into the travel case, how stupid is that!?! I can see this cable being the 1st thing I lose on a business trip because it does not have a place to be stored.

Gosh, I wanted to love using this shaver. I was excited and wanted to prove all these other bad reviews wrong. Sadly, they are correct in every way.

My guess is many of the good reviews are being written by persons who have not had the pleasure of trying one of Norelco's older shavers to notice the amazing quality they can provide. Folks, do yourself a favor and get an older model, preferably something from the late 90's IMHO.

Norelco, come'on buddy.. Your losing me big time here.

It's back to my 5885xl, and I have found my HQ5's here on Amazon, clicking buy; and it's byebye to my 1050x.

:(

F.

title: Banana Cream Pie Scent
text:
When I first tried this Marshmallow Vanishing Cr√®me in a sampler kit, I purchased five more kits and then a 1.5 ounce glass container of this product. Can I say it is addictive? Yes, I guess it does have a banana scent and the texture is similar to a banana cream pie topped with whipped cream.

To say this is decadent is an understatement. You will be very tempted to slather your entire body in a good helping of this cream. Fortunately, it goes a long way and absorbs extremely well. In fact, that is why they call it "vanishing" cr√®me. The ingredient list is impressive and contains rose water, mango butter, beeswax, grapeseed oil, rosehip seed oil, Vitamin E, marshmallow extract, willowbark extract, calendula flower extract, and a heady fragrance.

Grapeseed oil is one of the most powerful antioxidants and is high in proanthocyanidins, a group of bioflavonoids that are superior because they are water soluble. This ingredient also prevents skin cell damage caused by pollution and sun exposure.

"Marsh Mallow" is actually a pink flowering herb found in marshes and damp meadows. It has been used for centuries as a food and a medicine. The leaves and roots secrete an emollient fluid with healing properties for inflamed skin. In the past, people boiled the roots in wine to make a cough remedy.

I found this luscious creamy dreamy product to be healing for the body and mind. Not only will you feel comforted by nature, your skin will be baby soft and this product can be used for all-over body healing. The silver lid and glass jar have an unusually cute appeal. If you love this product, you might want to try the Pore-refining mask, Evening Primrose Overnight Cr√®me and the very unique parsley blemish stick. To take luxury to the next level, try the Shea Butter Decollete Cr√®me on your feet, hands or all over your entire body. What an amazing line of products. They heal, protect and soothe your mind.

I'm still trying all the Burt's Bees products, and love how these products make me feel. They add a level of protection to your skin care routine and the clay mask I recently tried cleaned my pores like a dream.

~The Rebecca Review

title: usually four to six shampoos and is great for blending away grey (If there are only a ...
text:
I applied the color according to directions. I found the color to be watery and whenever I squeezed or applied the color it ran down the side of the bottle and my wrist. My hair is natural medium dark brown with natural cinnamon color highlights. Via Natural Hair Color gave me true dark brown hair color. After coloring my hair was healthy looking and radiant. After four days, the color is still true and no rub off of color.

Most semi-permanent hair color contains no ammonia, no peroxide, no alcohol and is similar to temporary hair color. Therefore, can be applied directly from the bottle. Semi-permanent hair color does not penetrate the cuticle. It is more of a hair tint then color. The color is only deposited on the outside of the hair. However, the color typically starts to fade in about six to eight shampoos. Unlike temporary hair color, it lasts longer, usually four to six shampoos and is great for blending away grey (If there are only a few grey hairs the color is more effective) and perfect if you don‚Äôt like commitment.

Via Natural Hair Color has many hair nutrients, Vitamin E C&H UV Proteins for your hair, and protection from sunlight and pollutants for your hair. Via Natural Hair color, is so gentle, it can be used directly after relaxing (chemical processing). It leaves your hair conditioned, silky and shiny, with vibrant.

title: bulbs are cheap
text:
Sent it back because you can't get a non-broken lightbulb? That's pretty silly, the cost of shipping it back was probably more than the cost to go to the hardware store and buy a $.75 bulb. I agree that they did a poor job of shipping the replacement, but you will break or burn-out the bulbs eventually anyway... So suck it up and go buy a bulb.

And for the reviewer complaining about the focal distance... The magnification rate and focal legnth are tied together by the laws that govern the optical properties of a magnifying lense. Any simple single element lense of the same power will have the same focal distance. You need a binocular or telescope to magnify with this sort of power at a longer distance, that means more weight, and compound lenses. They do make such devices, microsurgeons have them, and people with really poor eyesight sometimes need them. Another option is to tell an eyedoctor what you want and get a perscription for some progressive lenses with a variable focal legnth... but magnification will drop off quickly as objects are farther out, after all this is another simple single element lense again.

This unit does what it is supposed to do, though the headlights are kinda crappy with regard to their aim... But you can get the bulbs to aim better if you adjust them a bit, or use different bulbs that have a wider dispersion pattern... or just turn them off and use a good worklight.

title: Easy to use, but you must use oil in your hair to moisturize!
text: Very easy to use! Just brush hair slowly in deliberate strokes and straightens fine hair in two strokes at 180 degrees. I have to use" Enjoy Oil" on my hair after shampoo and cream rinse. I have to still use the oil because my hair is so dry from coloring.  I leave the oil in while my hair dries. Once my hair is completely dry, the Straightening Brush takes about one minute to heat up to 180 degrees. Then I straighten my hair with one or two deliberate strokes at 180 degrees. title: STICKY SITUATION
text:
When I first received the item I was pretty excited. Tried opening it out of the outer plastic bag, but it was sticky. I thought it might have been a leak, and sure enough the product had sticky goo all over the cardboard packaging. It was pretty bad even for a leak, so I examined it over the sink, but then realized the ENTIRE top half of the spirit gum adhesive bottle had broken off and half the glue was filling the clear plastic cover attached to the cardboard.

At this point I was worried about glass cuts but I tried to salvage what remained of the glue. Using a scissor, I tried extracting the glue remover so at least I can use it to clean up all the stickiness resulting from the sticky situation. When I cut the packaging open, all the glue started dripping out into the sink. Long story short, the glue got everywhere and it was a mess cleaning up because THE REMOVER DIDN'T WORK EITHER! As there was a lot of glue, I also applied the remover liberally, including pouring out enough to cover my hand and soaking a cloth to scrape with. I had to later resort to using citric acid using lemons and that seemed to work better but still tough to remove.

I considered buying a new one but at that point I really didn't think it was worth it given my experience. All in all it took maybe 2 hours to clean up, and to begin with I have an extreme dislike for sticky substances on my hands.

title: I wanted to love these...
text:
I really did want to love these. I had to cut off a bunch of hair after a bleach accident, and I HATE having short hair, so I've been curling it just to make it a little less awful. I obviously don't want to use heat when I'm trying to nurse my hair back to health, so my only real option is sleeping in curlers. Foam rods make great curls, but they are horribly uncomfortable, and my hair is too slippery for rag curlers when it's this short. These looked like a happy medium.

These are pretty easy to use - they roll well, and the wires keep them in place pretty well. They are much, much more comfortable to sleep in than foam rods. I understand that they have to be squishy to be comfortable; however they are just too small! I tried them every night for two weeks, and I never got the curls I wanted. They almost always ended up much too tight, except when I tried rolling larger sections, which ended up really uneven - tight in places and barely curled in others. I'm going for a defined curl, not soft waves, but these were ridiculous.

I ended up removing the foam and replacing it with cut-up foam rods, which was a slight improvement over just the foam rods. I'm currently testing (second night) foam rods that are very big but made of super squishy, comfortable foam. If they don't work, I'll go back to the hybrid of these and fosm rods til I find something better, do they aren't totally worthless, but I wouldn't buy them again.

I could fry it with a curling iron, and within minutes it was flat again, so I just gave up and have always had very boring hair. I got this knowing that if it didn't work, at least it wouldn't damage my hair, so it was worth a try. I showered and let my hair air dry for a little bit, but while it was still damp, I followed the instructions, and on the second attempt, it looked right and felt secure. I put a sleeping cap on for the night. It was only slightly awkward sleeping on it at first, but I slept well. In the morning, I took out the curler, which was just as simple as putting it in, and was shocked! I didn't have to do anything to make the curls look good. I even combed through the curls, and they bounced right back. At the end of the day, they were just as curly as the morning. No hair spray, no special products, no nothing. Very impressed!

title: Great set!
text:
Love these stamping plates! There is tons of variety and most images stamp great! There have been maybe one or two portions of the buffet style that I have a hard time to get to stamp, one part specifically is the bike but I haven't given up on it yet!

The packaging is nice though I wish they would have sealed the back since its a product that is going to be worked on with acetone I actually rubbed the logo partially off of one of them! But that's purly cosmetic and clearly doesn't affect how it stamps.

I have had no problem getting corner images to stamp like some seem to, I may have to scrape it a different way than up and down but I have been able to get corners to stamp great!

The scraper and stamper that come with this set are also wonderful. I was not counting on much from the previous set reviews but they seemed to have changed the way the package the stamper so it was not damages at all. It's a very nice squishy and slightly sticky stamper, I had to prime it very lightly with a extra fine file but after I did that it picks everything up! The scraper is also my new go to scraper, I like it better than just a gift card and especially more than a metal scraper.

Overall I'm very happy with this and definitely wouldn't hesitate to order other sets from them. The only reason this didn't make it to a 5 star for me was because of some of the shallow etching mentioned above and the way the back if the plates were designed.

title: This is such a convenient and easy to use product
text:
This is such a convenient and easy to use product. I have pretty straight hair, but there are days I wake up and am just a mess. This is great for those days. It heats up just as quickly as my straightener and makes quick work of my weird hair flips. The rubber nubs keep the heat off my scalp, and it is easy to control where you put it.

My only complaint is that trying to straighten hair that hasn't been brushed is difficult, so make sure you brush your hair first. It also tends to leave my hair a bit frizzy, so I have to use smoothie cream to counteract that.

All in all I am very glad I have this as a tool in my beauty arsenal.

I received this product at a discount in exchange for an honest and unbiased review.

title: Might be helpful, but not spectacular
text:
I am cautiously optimistic that this product will be helpful, but it's hard to say since I can't scientifically compare the "after" to the "before" . I've been using it for about a month. It certainly does no harm and might do some good, but to say that it's miraculous is a bit of an over statement.

My hair is damaged from old age and too many medications. The newer the hair, the less dry and damaged it appears. The tips are terribly dry, but it seems to me that, since using this product they are a little bit more flexible and maybe softer in texture but no different in appearance.

The shampoo lathers well and I leave it on for a few minutes while I bathe to let it soak in. However, since I can't find an Argan Oil Conditioner that doesn't have to be washed as in shampooed) out I'm not using a conditioner. It seems to me that having to shampoo, then add a conditioner, and have to shampoo it out is more time consuming than necessary. I haven't used any of my non-argan oil conditioners because I'm afraid they might undo whatever the shampoo is supposed to have done. To me, the idea combination is a shampoo and rinse-out conditioner that are meant to compliment each other.

title: Works great but has parabens
text:
I need a waterproof eyeliner because make up tends to smudge really easily on my eyes (I'm Asian & I have eczema around my eyes so I tend to over moisturize them). The women at the makeup counter suggested this after I saw the waterproof liquid liner I used with MAC was discontinued. It lasts forever & you definitely need remover to remove it (which is the way I like it) and in the rare moment it does somehow come off, it fades off rather than flaking. It also gives a really nice CRISP line, which is what I want.

But it has parabens, which have been found in breast cancer tumors. The Cosmetic Ingredient Review & the FDA have found parabens to be safe but I don't really trust either (the CIR is sponsored BY the industry it reviews, hm). There's been no proven link and the study that found the parabens didn't study how much parabens are in normal tissue. So it's really up to you if you care about parabens in your products. Honestly, if it was $4-8, I would probably not care...but for $24, C'MON SON. Had to return.

This is not a big deal though as you can fill it manually with the nivea lotion bottle. Also it comes with a smaller travel charger base which I prefer anyways as the refill station is enormous and takes up too much counter space. As other reviewers have pointed out this is really not a razor to use in the car. It is meant to be used wet and with the Nivea lotion since when used without hair clippings will go everywhere. I found when using soap and the lotion I do not have a problem with clippings. In the manual on page 22 it states: "This razor has no hair collection chamber to capture stubble. To prevent stubble from falling, apply sufficient shaving conditioner while shaving." If you don't intend to use moisturizer with this system then you would probably be better off buying a product that is not designed for it. So far though I love the product and it is one of the closest shaves I ever had. On a side note I only paid $109 when I purchased mine. The current price I think is a little high. Awesome product highly recommend it!

title: Gorgeous Hair Extensions
text:
I've been wanting to try tape in extensions and see how well they would do in my baby fine thin hair. In the past, sew in and clip in extensions pulled the hair from my scalp. The salon I got to charges over $300 for a set so I was hesitant to spend that kind of money if it wasn't going to work well for me.

I decided to get these so I could try them before spending hundreds at the salon. They came quickly and are really wonderful quality hair. They are super soft and come with everything you need to put them in yourself-the hair pieces, tapes and a comb. I watched a few youtube videos to make sure I wouldn't screw it up. I wanted to add them just to the sides of my head, where I'm thinnest to see how I liked using/wearing them. The application was super easy. I am so surprised how easy this is to do yourself at least on the sides of your head. The back of the head will be a challenge but have a friend help you out. These also come with additional adhesive in case of any mistakes. There are only 20 pieces which create 10 hair pieces because you sandwich your hair between two loose hair pieces. So if you want a thicker look or have thick hair you'll want to order two boxes.

I'm super pleased with these and will order more when these need replaced.

title: Great...BUT Beware of Size Issues
text:
EDIT - I wrote the review below and then I realized that each page has it's specific style AND varied SIZES. I didn't realize this at first. This fact alone will lead me to not buy them again. It's common to mess up on ONE brow in a pair. Its nice to be able to go to your page and just cut off a new one and not worry if it's the same size as the others. I only like the bigger (longer) brows, so I won't even want to use half the brows on each page. Major issue for me. I'll leave the tips below, because if you don't care about size differences, maybe this info will help you.

1- They are overall amazing!
2- They take some practice, but it's worth it.
3- When I mess up, I remove them with alcohol and toilet tissue. I wet it with alcohol and rub with dry toilet tissue. The dry helps rub the transfer off. It's not super pleasant, but it works.
5- They last for me for two full days.
6- As crazy as it sounds, I followed the advice of someone here and shaved my (small) brows after trying to apply over my natural brows. I was very freaked out about shaving my brows, but my brows sucked anyhow and it improved the look of these by far!
7- My advice is to try all or almost all of the varieties sent in the package. It can't hurt to try, right?! Remember you can always remove them if you really can't stand them. Some of the ones that looked very odd on paper, looked not bad on me! Some look better on "natural" days and some look better with make-up. I wear the ones I don't hate on days I'm just staying home and I save my favs for the days I go out.
8- The eyebrow print is on the front AND the back, so you can hold them up in the mirror to place correctly. Super helpful.
9- Again, overall these look very natural! To eliminate the shiny look they can have a little brush of power foundation works, but I have found that a little water splashed on my face after helps too.

title: Sweet smell, not too greasy
text:
I've never used a scalp treatment before and wasn't sure what to expect. I got this serum for my niece. She's 3 and suffers from lingering cradle cap. We've tried a lot to get rid of it without much luck. I was very happy this serum is verified organic because we're very mindful of the products used on her.

The serum has a slightly sweet smell, but isn't over powering. We've been using the serum on her twice a week for about 3 weeks now. The serum goes on easily and doesn't make her hair too greasy. What we've noticed with her scalp has less big flakes, less irritation and less itching. Our intention is to keep using the serum and our hope is that continued use will yield more progress with her cradle cap. I'd recommend this serum for anyone with dry, itchy scalp or cradle cap. I received this product for free for my honest opinion and unbiased review. I am in no way associated with this seller nor am I obligated to leave positive feedback.

title: For a soft beard, and a great value, you can't go wrong.
text:
This is my first foray into the use of beard oil. Over recent months, as I grew my goatee longer, I started noticing some flakiness on my chin (always clean and well groomed), and that my beard hairs were becoming drier and stiff. It seems time is against me, as the gray hairs in my beard are noticeably stiffer and scratchier. After reading reviews of several products, I chose the Fragrance Free Beardsmen Beard Oil. I didn't want any scent that would compete with anything else I chose to wear. I specifically chose Beardsmen after comparing ingredients with other brands. Formulations were similar, all using several types of natural oils to create a moisturizing product. Two things convinced me to try Beardsmen. First, the quantity. For less money than some other products, Beardsmen offers a much larger quantity of oil than pretty much anyone, so they definitely win the "bang for the buck" award. Second, Beardsmen is the only one that has a flow controlling dispenser, so you don't have to mess with ridiculous eye droppers and such. Oh... and the product itself? I LOVE it. No more flaky chin skin, and my beard is soft and smooth. This is obviously a plus as far as my wife is concerned. There is only the very slightest hint of a light "oil" smell when you first put it on, which is not strong enough be more than barely noticeable for a second or two, and definitely would never be noticed by others. After using this for about a month, and giving a small quantity to a friend to try, I still have most of the bottle full. This stuff will last forever, and when you finally do run out, you'll likely panic and jump on Amazon to get another bottle. I know I will.

UPDATE: After a little thought, I tried a small experiment, that worked out well. I carefully pried the dispenser plug out of the bottle and put a few drops of my favorite cologne into the unscented beard oil, then replaced the plug. Now I have this great beard oil that smells very nice as well.

Use: Easy use but I wish the drill didn't turn on with a switch but rather with a button where the thumb would be when holding the product. Allows for more control of the tool as opposed to using both hands to turn the machine on and off.

Product: All drill bits shown were included and great but they weren't as "sharp" as a professional would want. If you wanted to file of the edge of an acrylic nail to shorten it, it would take a little more time but overall it's not that much weaker.

The bits: You have to unscrew the top to remove the bits which is a bit of a hassle since you can't easily take it on and off but no big deal if you're using the tool on yourself and not a client.

The charger: It sucks. It's a really short cord so you need to sit really close to a wall switch.

Overall it's a great starter kit especially for the price so I'm satisfied and look forward to using the product. I would recommend to people who plan on doing their own nails but not for professionals who want to work on clients.

title: Didn't work for me
text:
I almost never write reviews, but feel compelled to on this one. I took a chance on this and haven't seen any results yet. Granted I'm not super close to a six pack, but just wanted to lose some the of abdominal fat.

Also, when I received my product, I noticed that it was sold from a Jeffrey A Bolter.

Looking back at the 5 star reviews: the first is from Jeffrey. the second from A. Bolter, the third from Adam. And all three of these are the only reviews written by them.

Coincidence? maybe. maybe not.

Take my review with a grain of salt, maybe it'll work for you. The smell is pleasant. However, I won't be ordering again.

----------------------------------------------------------
UPDATE 3/11

All 3 of the 5 star reviews I mentioned have now been deleted. Which now makes me certain that they came from the seller!

I guess the moral is you can't really trust any non-verified purchases. The more I think about it even some of the verified purchase ones might be questionable. Clearly the seller has seen my original review (and will see this one) and will probably verify some purchases in order to give 5 star reviews. Sad because I guess I naively do trust these reviews on Amazon. Going forward I'm really going to pay attention more to the 1-3 star reviews.

Just consider yourself warned. Buyer Beware.

title: Smells Wonderful, Good Lotion For Dry Skin
text:
It's nearly summer here in New England, which means lots of time swimming and sunning. As a result, quality lotions are needed. That is why I requested this one. This review is of: Spanature Aloe Vera Hand & Body Lotion Travel Size Selection Made In Korea 75 ml/2.53oz (4pcs)‚Ä¶

As the product information states, this comes as four cute boxes of lotion, great for gift giving. Inside the boxes, all four tubes of lotion do have foil caps, so your safety was considered.

The lotion itself smells light and airy to me, not heavy. It's also not very thick, and for that reason I do not like it as a hand lotion. I'm washing my hands all the time and I really need something thick to really moisturize and coat my hands. However, for a body that's been in the sun and/or water, this lotion is absolutely perfect and quite effective. It's a bit thin as I said, but it absorbs quickly and seems to last for at least 3-4 hours. (I am talking really dry skin here, so for you, it would probably last longer.)

Overall, I'm very pleased with this Spanature Lotion. I think these would make for a nice small gift or stocking stuffer, or of course, a gift to yourself.

title: Amazing!  It works and my teeth are not sensitive!
text:
This product is amazing! After using it for one evening (you do 4 cycles each time you use it) I could see a substantial difference. My teeth look as white as they did years ago. I am a coffee drinker and enjoy fruit such as cherries... both of which can stain your teeth significantly. My teeth are not at all sensitive from this product.
Make sure you use the protective lip care before each treatment cycle. You have to use it on your lips and inside your lips. I think it is because of the gel you apply to your teeth. I didn't get it on the inside for a cycle and the inside of my lip was a bit sensitive for a few hours. But I also have extremely sensitive skin. It felt fine later that day.
As far as the fit of the "universal" tray. For me, it's not a great fit, but I think that is because I had 4 adult teeth pulled when I was a kid (my mouth was too small and my orthodontist had not started using palatal expanders). So I need to hold the tray in with one hand... which is a bit tedious, but totally worth it.
I will definitely continue using this product.

Even the slightest touch of the lash to the eyeliner will have it STUCK! The eyeliner also is very water and smudge proof!

I have only taken one star off because the lash band itself can be a little bit irritating for people with small eyelids/monolids. While wearing these lashes, the inner corner of my eyes were feeling a bit irritated because the band was poking the skin. Eventually this made my eye water, and the inner corners of the eyelash were beginning to peel up. I feel that if I readjusted these lashes, or cut some portion off, it would help with the issue.

title: Does not fit recessed aerator faucets.
text:
This Seller needs to tell prospective Buyers that this product DOES NOT FIT the newer designer faucets that have recessed aerators, which are the most popular faucets now days. These are not like simple the aerators on other faucets. It's recessed and screws up inside the faucet tip. Standard aerators are just screwed on to the end of the faucet tip and can easily be removed by unscrewing them with a pair of pliers. My Delta faucet needs a special key/wrench to remove the aerator that you can purchase on Amazon, but it's likely this product won't fit anyway, based on the other reviews I read.

I really wanted this product to work, because I have a Shower Breeze (purchased on Amazon) attached to my shower head, and I love it. This product looked identical but made for sink faucets. The Seller needs to make an adaptor that fits recessed aerator faucets since none are available. I returned this item.
