title: Cue the squeals of delight: rose-shaped cleansing foam is basic, but big on the cute factor
text:
OK first of all, I did not pay an outrageous price for this. Only $16 usd at a Hong Kong drugstore chain called Mannings. This foam is pure visual pleasure -- shake the pressurized can, and press down on the sides to expel a rose-shaped dollop of cleansing foam. Cue the squeals of delight and instagram envy from beauty junkies.

The foam itself does not remove makeup -- you'll still have to use a cleansing oil first. It's more of a 2nd step cleanser in your dual cleansing routine. If it were not in the shape of a rose, i highly doubt re-buying this --the performance is quite ordinary/basic. But the ROSE! adorable.

For me, the visual gimmick wore off after a while, and I found myself using a normal cleansing foam in a tube, as it was faster and easier than using two hands to pump out the rose each time. Fun to experience one time, but not a re-buy for me.

title: Natural look, natural product
text:
I purchased this from Carbon Beauty when it was sold out online at Sephora. I have tried many different brow products, including Anastasia, and find EcoBrow delivers the most natural appearing, long-lasting results. It's easy to build your brow to the color depth and shape that suits you. Any mistakes are easily corrected with a damp Q-tip. It lasts throughout the day, no touch-ups needed.

The pot of color seems very small at first. But so little is used that I expect this to last a long time.

A word about application. I also purchased the EcoBrow defining brush. I would recommend its purchase as well. The brush tip is firm, which makes application more precise, and the spoolie does not bend. I have a brow brush from Lanc√¥me. It is softer and didn't give the control that the defining brush did.

A word about color. The color swatches are deceiving since the pot of creme is so concentrated. Do pay attention to the hair color description provided. I did not, and first purchased Sharon. This was a bit too light with a red undertone, not quite right for my dark brown hair. I then paid attention and purchased Liz. She was a perfect match for my dark brown hair.

text:
This is definitely one of those products that I absolutely don‚Äôt need and didn‚Äôt know it existed, but now that I have one and know it exists, I love it and don‚Äôt want to let it go.
Honestly, this product is incredibly simple - it‚Äôs just a tube with a base, and even the base probably isn‚Äôt completely necessary.This particular holder comes with the tube and base connected and the open end of the tube facing down, so you‚Äôre unable to store anything inside of it unless you use it upside down, but then you couldn‚Äôt grab scrunchies off of it as easily. The strange thing about it is that the bottom of the base has some kind of brown paper on it - it looks like it should be removable, but it‚Äôs not. Honestly, since I‚Äôll be keeping scrunchies on this pretty much all the time this will likely remain covered, but I still don‚Äôt like it. I would also like it better if the diameter of the tube was slightly smaller so some of my ties that are slightly smaller don‚Äôt get stretched out, but I can work with this. I‚Äôm very happy it fits perfectly on my bookcase where I wanted it to go, and I also really love that even though it‚Äôs only $10, it comes with eight scrunchies to get you started. I‚Äôve been using one of these scrunchies all week and so far it‚Äôs holding up well - while I thought I wouldn‚Äôt like the material, it actually feels way nicer than it looks. I‚Äôm very happy with this product and am considering getting more as gifts for others later this year, if it holds up. I did get mine to use for scrunchies as the listing suggests, but you could also definitely use it for other things such as bracelets - it‚Äôs quite simple, but convenient.

title: Best cordless trimmer on the market...period
text:
For those of you who say this trimmer doesn't cut/shave close, it's probably because you are using it wrong.

1. You NEED to zero gap adjust the blade for these things to "hit". There is a tutorial on youtube that shows you how.
2. You need a rechargeable battery. I have me a pair of duracel rechargeables and it works wonders.
3. You need Cool care & blade oil for maintenance.

I've heard problems about the power switch, but I haven't had those problems personally. I've been using these trimmers specifically for travel to keep my shapeup/lineup crispy. I haven't had any issues with durability unlike the slimline pros. As far as I know, these trimmers are the most slept on, underrated in the cordless market.

I love the size of it. It's light on the hand and it's super powerful if you take intomaccount everything I mentioned earlier.

My only problem with this trimmer is the housing curvature that can get in the way of the blade sometimes.
Still needs some more tweaking by the Wahl company, and i agree with the naming. They went from bling to g whiz...the names keep getting corny.

This little thing gets a B+.

title: Good for what you pay for
text:
I like to fashion myself as sort of a cologne connoisseur‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.a man‚Äôs man who just really likes to smell good all the time. I began wearing cologne shortly after I started my first job in high school, and ever since then I have been enamored with finding great smelling colognes. When I saw this cologne, and I read what it was inspired by, I felt that it was almost a must have for me.

The first and most obvious reason most of us on here purchased this cologne is because it is inspired by Ralph Lauren Polo Red; and since that cologne is fairly pricey, undoubtedly most of us felt they were going to get a sweet deal. Now, you may ask what is the difference between this and the legitimate cologne that you would pay 60$ or more for?

The first thing to know is that this cologne does not smell exactly like Polo Red at all. In fact, it is very loosely inspired by the actual scent. I challenge anyone to buy and smell the original cologne, then buy and smell this and tell me it‚Äôs exactly the same thing. Sorry folks, this just isn‚Äôt the same smell. It does, however, share similarities with the Polo Red‚Ä¶..which makes it enticing, but it just is not the same thing.

The main issue that I have with this cologne is that it simply does not last more than an hour at best. I now understand why you get a 3.0-ounce bottle for 15$, and that is because you are constantly reapplying it to keep the smell fresh. With a normal (and quality) cologne I can go pretty much the extent of my eight-hour shift at work and still smell relatively fresh, but this cologne honestly started fading at about 20-30 minutes after application.

In the end this may not bother folks who just want something cheap to make them smell good for a little while. Heck, even I like the way it smells at first. The problem for those of us who fashion ourselves fragrance snobs is that the scent just fades away too quickly.

If affordability is what you look for in a cologne, then by all means this is your product. I, however, would just suggest spending the extra couple of bucks and buying the real deal. I can‚Äôt see how anyone would be disappointed with that at all.

title: Ejection system works well but times are actually too long for long haired cats.
text:
So I have a cat which is probably classified as a Norwegian forest cat breed with very long hair. And I really need to comb him to ensure I can get whatever hair he sheds to control hairballs. This brush does do a fairly good job but with my cat specifically the problem is that the tines are all bent in one direction. Because of this you have to draw the brush downward on the cat in a smooth motion where the handle is always oriented downward in a line with your stroke. By that I mean you can't hold the brush sideways or you can't pull the brush upside down and just use it any direction you want you must always draw the brush downward in direction consistent with the handle, because else the bent tips work against you.

On top of that the tines are actually a little overly long. I found that if I partially engage the ejection button but I can much more easily brush my cat because it artificially shortens the tines. When the tines are fully engaged I basically catch too much and the they end up trying to bend versus navigate their way through the fur.

It's possible that I'll be forced to switch to a normal bristle brush and try that but I have had high hopes for this because I'm used to using stiff brushes in order to remove excess fur from pets before.

So I guess if I have one complaint it would be basically that I wish the times weren't bent and we're about 30% shorter. Then I could move the brush and any orientation I want and for my pet it would work very well. The deeper tines tend to get just caught and don't drag through the fur as easily.

title: Impressively effective
text:
I'm really impressed with this 100% natural nail polish remover from Pure Body Naturals. I love that it doesn't dry out my nails and cuticles and that it doesn't have an overpowering chemical odor like some other nail polish removers. Also, since my little girl likes to have her nails painted, I really appreciate the non-toxic nature of this product. It did struggle a little bit with removing glitter polish (as is to be expected with any nail polish remover), but successfully removed it with only a little effort. It does leave a bit of an oily film behind, which is nice to moisturize the cuticles, but you will need to make sure your nails are clean of any residue before re-painting your nails. I really like the dropper as well, as it dispenses just the right amount of nail polish remover onto a cotton ball very easily and without creating a mess.

I purchased this product at a promotional discount for evaluation purposes. Overall, I am very satisfied with this nail polish remover. I would highly recommend this product to others, and I plan to repurchase for myself in the future.

title: I'm Impressed Enough to Write About It
text: One of our cats has a problem with furballs, so we have tried and used a variety of grooming items, with probably five different slicker brushes alone. The cat that allows this slicker brush dislikes almost every version of grooming, so I‚Äôm massively impressed.  The other cat now seeks out being brushed and is quite insistent when someone sits near this brush versus his other usual grooming spot with a different item.  The bristles are quite strong, so if you have sensitive skinned hands, I‚Äôd recommend using an oven mitt or something similar when removing hair.  I prefer dog brushes because they‚Äôre usually larger, which works better on my cats usually, and this slicker has one of the largest brush areas out of all of the large brushes I have tried.  I didn‚Äôt think I‚Äôd be impressed enough with a grooming tool to want to write a review, but for something so simple, this is a really well-done slicker brush.

title: so I am satisfied with this cream

The smell is a little different. It was musky to me. It doesn't smell bad.. but it could be better. The size is probably enough for a few months, I still have tons so a little goes a long way. The only thing I didn't like about this was the fragrance, the scent is not a scent I would normally wear but since it does seem to benefit my breasts it
Is a scent I can live with, I just spray perfume over my shirt and it covers it up.

Overall I am happy about this cream, even with the change being suttle so far it still has some affect and that's better than nothing for me. I'm hoping I see more improvement with this in the long run and I will continue using it.

title: Works great!
text: This worked much better than I expected it to. I put them on on a Wednesday morning, sat for 90 minutes, then took them off and rinsed my feet. They felt tight for a couple of hours, like my feet were too big for my skin, but it wasn't uncomfortable - just noticeable. I forgot about it for a couple of days, and by the Saturday after (so 4 days) HUGE chunks of skin were peeling off of my feet. I had an appointment for my first pedicure in a year on Sunday, and the technician was somewhat appalled at the amount of skin she was removing from my feet. Today is Monday, and despite the thorough job the pedicurist did removing the skin, I'm still peeling a bit. I expect this will be done in a couple of days, but the result is unbelievably smooth, soft feet. I will absolutely use these again (and will probably combine with a pedicure again so I don't have to do all the skin peeling myself). The only downside (and this is mentioned on the instructions) is that my feet are a lot more sensitive to temperature and sunlight. So walking around barefoot on the hot concrete at the pool is rather painful, and I had to use higher SPF sunscreen on my feet because the new skin felt like it was frying in the sun. It didn't burn, it was just uncomfortable. Overall, I'm very pleased with the product and will absolutely purchase again!

I have tried a number of these brushes. What I like about this one is that it goes down to 80C (176F). It was so cool that I was not sure it was on. I have fine hair, high porosity that is 5 months post-straightening relaxer. And, I find that light heat with a silicone-based glosser helps to gently close the cuticle and to keep my roots from tangling. What I don‚Äôt like is that this brush design does not have the round guiding bristles around the edges that help to pull your hair into the hearing plate. So, it feels like you are brushing your hair with your elbow and that it is not penetrating to the roots. You have to grip the hair with your other hand so it feels like you are only getting the shaft of your hair. So, the brush is best for people with longer hair who do not have curly roots or those who need the super low heat setting as an option.

If you would like to be able to rake the brush over your roots to tame curls at 250 F and up, other bushes to consider are https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07FGV9NQG/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_asin_title_o01_s00?ie=UTF8&th=1 or https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B071HFQGJX/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_asin_title_o00_s00?ie=UTF8&psc=1. Note - My glamfields brush malfunctioned after first use which is why I ended up trying this one, but I decided to give Glamfields another chance because it is great when it works - never had results like that before. title: Excellent - gentle and effective but...
text: This works exceptionally well for an aluminum-free alternative.  Most of the time, I will use Nivea antiperspirant once or twice a week, and supplement it with this deodorant. Antiperspirant seems to last through washes, so I don't need to apply it every day.  I don't have the kind of body that can go with using only deodorant, and often times even antiperspirant fails.  This Nivea deodorant really does work for getting rid of odor, and because it dried in the armpit, it seems to make a seal that stops sweat a bit.  One word of warning...this deodorant has a REALLY STRONG scent.  If you are bothered by fragrances, you may not like this at all.  It definitely clashes with perfume for a few hours of wear, and if applied at night, I found the fragrance to be annoying and it game me a headache. There are other aluminum-free Nivea formula with different fragrances that I'm going to try to see if their perfume is less pungent. Also - it smells like "deodorant" even though it's a fresh scent.  Anybody near to me could be thinking "Wow, she wears a lot of deodorant."

title: Not bad but there are better choices
text: This is the 2nd hair straightener I've had the opportunity to try.  The other is the Furiden Professional Hair Straightener Titanium Flat Iron.  I'm going to write this review as a comparison between the two since they are in the same price range.  For starters, both heat up quickly, have variable temperature settings, automatic shut off and a swivel cord.  The Autenpoo (who comes up with these brand names???) brand has a mechanical on/off switch that also serves as the heat selector.  I prefer this over the Furiden which has on/off buttons and up/down buttons to set the temp on a digital screen.  If I want, I can leave the Autenpo's dial set on the temp I want (the lowest setting it has), unplug it when I'm done, plug it in the next day and it will just turn on and go to my favorite temp.  With the Furiden, I have to hold a button down to turn it on and then hit the down button 4 or 5 times to go to the lowest temp.  The Autenpoo also comes with a comb, some hair clips to section your hair during styling and a heat protective glove, and has a slide lock to keep it shut when not in use.  In all other aspects however, I prefer the Furiden.  Autenpoo's cord is super thick bulky, seriously like a vacuum cleaner cord.  It will probably last forever but adds unnecessary bulk and weight which would be especially problematic for traveling.  The main advantage Furiden has is the pointed end.  Not only is it better suited to tight areas close to your scalp or neckline but it can also help section your hair without needing a comb or your fingers.  Furthermore, the plates, which are longer overall, extend into the pointed tip to get the heat right where you need it.  Both of these irons do a perfectly fine job, but I just find the Furiden easier to use.

title: Beyond my expectations
text: So even though I used to do hair and should know about magnetic eyelashes, I didn‚Äôt and I was SO skeptical. I finally decided to try them. These things exceeded my expectations by far! The first time I chose the not so dramatic ones but they were thicker than my own. They did great. They were only a tad heavy. They stayed on 8 hours but I took the eyeliner with me to work and touched them up. I honestly think they would‚Äôve stayed on longer if I hadn‚Äôt have forgotten and put regular eyeliner on first out of habit. I do wish this came in another color besides black as I have blonde hair and it‚Äôs dramatic. But once I wore them a while I realized it looked good. After work, I removed them easily. My eyes were itchy a little but when I woke up that evening they were back to normal. Another reason I think they didn‚Äôt stay on 12 hours was instead of following directions, I read somewhere that a person put the eyeliner on the the lashes while still wet and it worked better. The next night I followed directions. Put a coat on let dry then add another coat. Honestly, it pretty much dries by the time you finish both eyes. Don‚Äôt forget to shake it up though. They were very easy and quick to do. The only real time it takes is deciding which ones to use as there are so many nice selections. I realized the ones I thought were too dramatic when choosing actually look the best. I‚Äôve gotten o many complements. And this time they stayed on all night. I think I could sleep in them and they would stay on. I wouldn‚Äôt though. The corners might poke your skin on inner eye when you close them but this can be remedied by snipping a tad off with scissors once you try them on and see how they do. I didn‚Äôt have to trim mine. Also, I had put a pair on and decided I liked the longer ones better so I took off the first ones and applied the others. I never redid the eyeliner. They still worked and stayed on. There‚Äôs magnet particles on eyeliner and the lashes are on a magnet strip. They are easy to remove but stay on like they are real. That sounds crazy. I didn‚Äôt want to ruin my own lashes with the glue kind plus I can‚Äôt get them on good enough without adjusting them. These you can take off and adjust. This gave me confidence I lacked in doing this. Plus, my hands aren‚Äôt that steady. When removing, start at corner and peel off. They won‚Äôt hurt your lashes. To remove eyeliner I used cold cream. It worked well. Just water doesn‚Äôt work. It is waterproof very much so. So cry all you want with these lashes ladies. You won‚Äôt have to worry about them falling off. One last thing, my skin is sensitive but they haven‚Äôt really bothered me so that is a big plus.

title: Shows AMAZING color on brown hair!
text:
I love love LOVE this dye!!!!
(TL;DR at bottom)
I have medium to dark brown hair, and the thought of bleaching it terrifies me because the last time I bleached my hair in high school I absolutely FRIED it. I was pretty hesitant to see how well this pink would show up on my dark hair without bleaching it first. Boy was I surprised.
First of all, I have a LOT of hair. I needed 3 bottles of dye to cover my whole head. Hopefully you can use my photos to compare your hair length to mine and use what I said to help you determine how many bottles you‚Äôd need to buy.
I didn‚Äôt just pour it in my hands and rub it all over my hair, I actually sectioned out my hair piece by piece to make sure I got the dye on every last bit of hair as evenly as possible. This whole process took about 2 hours. Yes, it was exactly as awful as it sounds. Man were my arms tired.. After I finished dying it, I put all of my hair up in a shower cap / bonnet and let it sit for 5 whole hours. Excessive? Probably lol.
I swear I remember hearing once a long time ago that when you wash out hair dye in the shower you‚Äôre supposed to keep washing it til the water runs clear. Well I was in the shower for a good 40 minutes shampooing the life outta my hair before I just gave up and got out the shower lol. My shower water continued to run pink every time I washed my hair for at least a good 2 to 3 weeks.
Oh and as for the washing?? Yeah I hate cold water so I never did any of that stuff that you‚Äôre supposed to do. I continued to shower every to every other day, and I used warm to hot water every time. Yeah yeah I know the color won‚Äôt last as long, but screw a cold shower. I also switched to using Herbal Essences Color Me Happy shampoo.
[EDIT: I am now aware that Color Me Happy is actually horrible for colored hair. That shampoo still contains SULFATES, which is the ENEMY OF HAIR DYE. So yeah make sure you read the ingredients on your shampoo bottles carefully, because clearly Herbal Essences is a bunch of LIARS.]
So after 1 month of warm showers and Herbal Essences, the third photo is what I was left with. I‚Äôm honestly incredibly happy!!! The pink definitely faded a lot, but there was still enough pink in my hair to the point where if a stranger on the street saw me they‚Äôd be able to say ‚Äúthat girl has pink(ish) hair.‚Äù This dye has exceeded all of my expectations.
One thing I‚Äôd like to add, though. This dye does seem to stain plastic showers. It kinda comes off when you scrub it with acetone (nail polish remover) and some abrasive cleaners. Over time the stains definitely do fade. But I just wanted to give y‚Äôall the heads up in case your shower turns pink and you can‚Äôt scrub it all off in one night.
I‚Äôm about to re-dye my hair with this same dye as soon as I finish writing this review, so it might even be brighter and last even longer this time!
~TL;DR~
1. Shows up great on medium brown hair, but I let it sit for 5 hours before washing.
2. Long hair (or at least mine) requires 3 bottles.
3. Stains plastic showers.
4. Color stays in nicely after a month of daily warm showers and using Herbal Essences Color Me Happy shampoo & conditioner.

title: This thing is the business
text:
I wasn't sure what to expect, but someone recommended this to me and I figured the price was right.

Well.

After one use, my skin is noticeably smoother and silkier. It's like magic. It's scratchy, yes, but not painfully so. Just scrubby-feeling. It's long, too, so you can get your back and shoulders no problem.

Highly recommend for anyone who'd like to get some good old-fashioned exfoliation while showering, without having to use scrubs or other products.

Don't forget to moisturize after you use it. Use lotion with lots of glycerin while your skin's still damp, and you'll be amazed at the results.

Wanted a specific size bowl to fit under the spout of my Komo grinder; and this fits perfectly, and is big enough that flour does not back up to the top. It is also attractive, light weight and pleasant to use. However, my sample came packaged in an open plastic bag (from which it, of course, came out of in transport), in a box with a few plastic air cushions. It also came with two gouges on the outside, which is not appreciated for something this expensive for what it is.
Update 4-8-17: Scratch aside, this bowl worked so well for my intended purpose that I bought a second one to use with my Nutrimill Harvest grinder at a different location. In this case I had to place the grinder on a bamboo coaster of the right size, that I happened to have handy, to get the spout to the right height. title: Anti-aging, acne scars, injuries, itching from bug bites and skin issues...this helps with all of it!
text: This is the second ice roller that I have purchased through Heaven's Bliss. I have many health related issues as side effects from past cancer treatments as well as fibromyalgia, chronic pain and permanent nerve damage all over my body and a bulging disc in my lower back... etc. I get unexplained muscle pain...same with my tendons, you name it..it will hurt at some point. I'm getting to the point that i am tired of taking all these chemicals and medications that only make me tired and cranky. I'd rather deal with the most of my pain with heat/ice therapy and massage (so long as it doesn't hurt my skin). I cannot tell you enough how much I absolutely love these rollers. And its a great idea to have more then one going in the freezer at all times. When I am hot and tired from a hot flash I can roll it on the back of my neck and on my face and I am instantly awake! Its refreshing! It helps all my muscle aches and pains that aren't helped with heat. I even used them last night when I was attacked by a swarm of Florida mosquitoes out in the yard. I was a mess....scratching my legs like crazy until I went and grabbed an ice roller and started rolling away all the itch and burn from the bites. One of my medicines makes bug bites leave huge welts on me and they itch and last for days and days longer than normal. Having had cancer twice like I have...I'd rather not use all those sprays and chemicals either. So I try to cover up and stay inside but sometimes you have to be out there in a hurry, like last night and well...you know the rest. I have been given the chance to purchase these Derma Ice Rollers at a discount for my unbiased and honest review. I honestly can't say anything bad about the product. They are just so handy and help with so many things!! It's also helped to reduce redness from my childs acne issues...just a wonderful invention overall!

title: Sensitive Girl Approved. Not perfect but overall okay!
text:
Excellent set of brushes with pretty good quality.
#1 rule when buying Bella and bear products: get on their email list for discount codes! I paid a little more than half of the current price for this set. Even at full price it's a good value (price per brush) but due to a few quirks I recommend not paying full price.
I'm a makeup junkie and own many brushes ranging from handmade very expensive Japanese brushes to easily accessible drug-store brand sets. I prefer synthetic brushes due to allergies and skin sensitives and I believe most of these are synthetic or blends.
The set arrived from Amazon in a very nice giftable thick sturdy box. I'm actually using the box and lid as liners in one of my makeup drawers.
I have broken down this review into two sections brushes and the case.
Brushes:
Handles are semi-matte black and the ferules are silver metal and appear to be crimped on which is very nice. The handles/ferules remind me of IT Cosmetics brushes. They are very well made, heavier constructed, and feature the company and brush name stamped on them.
Brush quality is good over all. Except for one of the brushes, they are all very soft and the density is appropriate for the applications.
Foundation, stippling, large shadow, and smudge shadow brushes are not evenly cut. There is noticeable uneven brush hairs with all 4 of these. The application with these particular brushes is okay but it's not as smooth as it would be with perfectly cut brushes.
The flat yellow brush is made of a taklon or nylon type material. It's large, thick, flat, and useless. It doesn't work with any kind of makeup in any kind of application because as soon as it touches skin, it splays, or splits. It's not flexible or functional. I have put it aside for craft applications, as it might work to pat on glue or something like that.
MY favorite brushes are the white shadow blending blushes, they work very well for blending shadow lines.
Runners up are the larger powder brushes for setting powder and bronzer/blush applications.
Even with the damage to the portfolio, some brushes are not cut properly, and one is useless, this is still an excellent value.
3-3.5 stars because the handle quality is really 4 star quality and most of the brushes are 4-5 star quality but there are some misses here too.
No issues with irritations or sensitivity which is very important to me.

Portfolio:
My large heavy portfolio arrived in fair condition. The zipper, doesn't work properly, and after opening I can't easily zip it again it. This is not a big deal for me because I will not be regularly using my brushes in this case. There was a pamphlet in the bottom of the box with brush descriptions and it made a permanent indentation in the case, which would be unfortunate if I was going to use the case for storage.
The larger brushes all came with mesh brush guards, the smaller brushes were wrapped in plastic.

text:
I've been using this serum semi-regularly(I rotate with other serums) for the past month or so and I absolutely love it. It's light weight, and sinks into the skin fast. I'm still in my 20's and I've pretty smooth skin so while I can't say much about its effect on wrinkles, I have a bit of sun spots and freckles and the serum has been doing its job evening out my skin tone. I've been using the serum only at night. After washing my face, I apply toner, then Olay regenerist serum, followed by two or three pumps of this Vitamin C serum, and finishing up with moisturizer (cream + oil). I also make sure to wear sunscreen during the day time. I have crazy dark circles from lack of sleep and the serum hasn't made much difference on them (I hadn't expected it to work on them) The only thing I didn't like about the product is that it has such a short shelf life - 3 months, but I guess it keeps the product at its highest quality + forces me to stick to my skin care regimen :]

title: Great value but silicone breaks
text: These clips are great!  I used to never section my hair - didn't know about it and wasn't sure of the point.  But then I realized that (1) I tended to do a good job at first and then rush though when I got tired and (2) unruly hair is easier to manage in small sections.  So, I use these clips daily to help keep my hair looking like I love myself.  Having so many is nice because I don't have to worry about losing some.  I also use them to keep my hair drying bonnet from opening up due to the air pressure.  And, I use them to hold my towel closed.  BUT, oftentimes, the silicone breaks.  So, I wanted a large quantity to help make up for this.  So, I deducted a star due to the lack of durability of the silicone - once it breaks, the hold feels much, much firmer. title: Not the best, not the worst, but a savior in times of Covid.
text:
I was disappointed when they arrived because the color was significantly darker than what is shown on the product page. Rather than golden blond and bleached blonde it was more like a mostly dark blond/light brown (with a reddish cast) with a little bit of bleached blond thrown in.

But I decided to work with it. I colored it lighter which ended up bringing out the red (not a good thing with my coloring), so I used a toner, and finally got to a point where they would blend in with my existing (and VERY spendy) extensions.

Although I don't look forward to spending $300 each time I have my existing extensions re-tightened and refreshed, it's a necessary evil and I'm not willing to go back to my thinning hair (radiation therapy, no thyroid, menopause and weight loss made me worry I'd wake up one morning looking like Jean Luc Picard.) But as the Covid months wore on, I found that an unanticipated benefit was that doing your own salon treatments at home saves a hella lot of money.

Fortunately, my husband was watching the first time I had my extensions installed. As I faced not being able to get them refreshed during lockdown, he suggested that I let him try removing the hangers-on and reinstalling the new ones. I was doubtful but fresh out of alternatives.

After watching every extensions installation video on youtube, he gave it a try. With some of my original extensions biting the dust during removal or the falling-out process, I needed a few extra to bolster the thickness, thus my purchase of these extensions.

PROS:
- Cheap. A fraction of the cost that I spent at my high end salon (which was over $1000 with initial installation). So, you can hardly argue with the cost.
- Once I got the color right, they seem to behave and feel the same as my existing pricey extensions.
- Shipped quickly.

CONS:
- Thinnish near the ends. Thickness peters out more than it should.
- Color significantly different from the thumbnail on the product page. (Probably less of a problem if you're not trying to match them to existing extensions and are not super picky about color.)
- Cheap enough to buy several and get a very thick mane o' hair.

WOULD I RECOMMEND?
Yes. With the caveat about color.

LONG STORY SHORT: I doubt I'll ever return to the pricey salon for extensions (unless these extensions don't stand the test of time.) Being able to buy these extensions and installation tools on Amazon, and being able to watch How To vids on youtube (and having a husband willing to do the deed) will probably save me about $2000 a year or more.

title: Jet Clean is a gimmick; any Norelco model is just as good
text:
If you don't own a Norelco triple-head razor, stop reading now and just buy one -- any one. Or if you own an ancient Norelco double-header, or a triple-header before the Lift'n'Cut heads, sure, get a new one. But if, like me, you have an old model, do your utmost to replace its parts and you'll be just as happy. (I replaced heads and two solder-tab NiCd's.) Here's why (echoing other reviewers' sentiments):
(i) This particular model is no faster than my old one, its "Speed XL" moniker notwithstanding. Maybe that's because of the new blade size/design, or maybe the old motor turns faster. (Seemingly, old AC and NiCd models spin faster than old NiMH models; YMMV.)
(ii) This model is no more adjustable (N/M/S) for closeness of shave than my old adjustable model (1-10). The heads do indeed rock more than the old spring suspension, but I still must stretch my skin with the other hand to get a close shave over the bumps.
(iii) The cleaning system leaves stubble-grit on the rubber bits. Also mine required repairs after 5 months, because the washer mechanism got stuck. (It has a 2-year warranty (yay!), alas they insisted on shipping the razor back, too (aargh!).) Norelco's attempt to "Gillette up a revenue stream" with consumables, i.e. cleanser fluid, is a little transparent.
(iv) The cleaning system leaves you with a damp razor, even if you shake it and let it stand for an entire day -- it's the shaving equivalent of a wet willie in the morning. Worse, the small quantity of liquid remaining is just enough to create a jumpy slide across the face -- not as even as completely dry, nor as smooth as a lubricated wet shave.

On the plus side, the battery life on this razor is excellent, and longer than old Norelcos. If you live out of a suitacase, you won't have to pack the cord. Which is good, because the charger circuit has been pulled out of the razor body and into a wall wart.

The razor rates 4 stars (not 5 because they have made better razors before, and hopefully will hence). The cleaning system gets 1 star. So don't get a CC model, but definitely do buy a Norelco razor. If you switch from blade or foil electric, please do as the manual says: give it two weeks of rotary use before judging the closeness of the shave. But especially if it's your first razor, grasshopper, you will be hooked for life!

title: Works great! Double beachy wave, Heatless curling system.
text: This works great! You just have to know how to use it correctly. The double curler band allows you to use less hair on each curler so that the hair dries faster and curls faster. Here IS MY 2 HOURS TO PRETTY CURLS METHOD: Part upper hair at crown of head,  and put hair from the upper head at crown,  in a pony tail for later. Snap the curling system closed, so that there is 2 round circle bands to use to curl with, and put both around head like a double crown head band. Push the top curling band where pont tail is for later use. Separate the bottom layer of hair into two parts... left side and right side and use only the bottom circle band curler for the bottom portion of head. Begin curling in left side by spritzing a little water onto the hair at root and curl it under band tucking it under and around curler one time only and then in next pass, grab a little more hair with it and continue going around the curler band. Keep spritzing new hair with water each time you pick up a new piece of hair and add that hair to the previous end of the one you just curled, until the whole left, bottom  side is done. Then start on the bottom right side of hair. When finished,  the  whole bottom curling band  will be filled with the hair from the lower portion of. Now it's time to take out the pony tail that was  on the grown of head  and put that hair under the second curling band and separate the left side of hair from the right. Start curling the left upper part of head as you did the bottom portion... spritzing small portion of hair with water at root and curling it once around the band and then pick up a little more new hair, spritz it with water and curl together with the former portion around band until all left side is done and now do right side. DO NOT SOAK HAIR.  Only LIGHTLY MIST IT a little with water or it wont dry in 2 hours. Dont curl too big a portion of hair at a time either, or it won't dry in two hours. Wait about 1 hour to 2 hours and remove curlers and you will get beachy type ringlets that are big. It takes about 10 minutes to wind hair around curlers. Lovely curls.

title: Small enough for airlines and trips to the store, great clip, good caps
text:
I bought these to fill with hand sanitizer and keep in my coat pockets (I'm in the NE so I don't go out without a coat). When I get home, I'm never in the same rush as I am when I leave, so I make a point of refilling them and replacing them as part of my get home routine (bring bags to the garage, wash hands, clean stuff in the garage, including sanitizer bottles, wash hands, refill sanitizer bottles, place in coat).

I use enough hand sanitizer that these small bottles are good for two days, at best, often just for one, but with my routine that is just fine. The bottles open and close easily and the caps fit tightly. The top is wide enough to fill easily. I've used the clip which is a good clip, but I generally just keep them in my coat pocket. I've not had any open accidentally nor have any leaked.

I'm very happy with this find.

UPDATE 2015-11-05: I received a replacement unit and didn't have any problems getting it on the hose this time. I did have to remove the black plastic piece that was already attached to the nozzle, and had to use a wrench because my hand wasn't strong enough to turn it. title: Brilliant Shaving Cream
text:
Truefitt & Hill Lavender is such a joy to use, it is downright therapeutic. A little bit goes a long way, and it's easy to create a nice lather. It feels very smooth and soothing. I get a close shave with little irritation. My skin feels better hydrated after using this than with most shaving creams.

Fragrance: The primary note is lavender, as you might have guessed. This lavender is masculine, and there is a bit of a "barbershop" smell. The effect is very relaxing and calming. This is not the sharp, pungent, synthetic lavender that you get with many cheap men's fragrances and grooming products. It is cool, natural smelling, and "round".

So far, this is the best cream I've used. It is also the most expensive, but well worth it. Other good choices are Proraso (not as good, but great price) and Taylor of Old Bond Street (close to the same shave quality, cheaper, smells decent). I have not tried Geo F. Trumper yet, so can't offer a comparison to that.

title: great product, I really truely believe in this and love it.
text:
I don't understand the bad reviews. If melatonin pills don't work for you then maybe it's just your brain chemistry, but this works better for me than any sleeping bill or melatonin pill and with the added benefit of relaxing my muscles in a similar way that an Epsom salt bath would. I'm not sure it makes me fall asleep necessarily, but I notice that my sleep is definitely deeper and I wake up feeling way more well rested and as if my sleep was richer and more effective. I really love it and keep a supply on hand always. It's great for airplane rides and right after you shower before bed.
I read one review here that someone said it was sticky and stayed on their skin, but then followed up with how they were on a vacation on an island and couldn't shower for 2 days. Haha, way to blame this great product for your bad travel choices. The lotion is not sticky and I really only just put a little on my index finger tip and thumb tip and give myself a neck massage with it to rub it in and on any other sore spots. That coupled with my firm mattress and I sleep so well.
Drink plenty of water througout the day, and don't drink any alcohol or beverages before bed and maybe try a warm soothing shower or bath before bed. Rub some of this lotion on the back of your neck and shoulders and in the soft skin spots like your elbow and knee pits so it will soak in well. You will have wonderful dreams and wake up feeling as if your REM sleep went deeper and longer than before. Don't look at electronics before bed and make sure you are sleeping in a cool dark room and are clearing your mind of worrying thoughts. It's really a great tool in your sleep tool box.
Remember that sleeping pills, especially crazy ones like ambien ... and alcohol too, are so bad for your sleep and sleep is the most important thing you can do for yourself. I love the fact that I really can go without coffee in the morning when I have a great long sleep. And my appetite totally changes and I crave health foods instead of unhealthy ones.

text:
This is a great little set of brushes for the price, but there are definitely some things that could be improved here. First, these really do apply foundation (liquid and powder) very well. I've used these with K-Beauty BB creams, stick foundations (Hourglass and FitMe), FitMe and Clinique liquid foundations, and BareMinerals powder foundation. Some of these require a beauty blend-type sponge on top to get a flawless finish, but most do not. I definitely use less product using these brushes, which has a bit of a learning curve - the first couple times I looked like a weirdo with way too much caked on. I mostly use the small round and the medium oval brush. The medium oval I use for foundation and sometimes cream contour/blush. The little round brush is AMAZING for cream shadows, especially ColourPop shadows.

These are very easy to clean and I haven't had problems with them shedding fibers after washing. This set comes with a nice little branded cotton bag for storage/travel. My *only* complaint about these is the solidity of the heads and their connection to the handles. Although mine haven't broken (yet) I feel like I have to be really gentle with these. The plastic creeks a bit when you use them and just feels fragile. I've thought about adding something like Sugru to the handles to make them sturdier, but for now they're holding up.

title: Sharper and thinner than other Floss Picks

The only thing that can be seen in a negative light is that the floss is not minty nor does it have any type of flavor.  This did not bother me, but, my daughter commented on it more than once.

title: Great oral irrigator - read this for a list of the adaptor sizes
text:
I purchased this SMAGREHO oral irrigator in March 2018. The water diverter is metal, as is one of the adaptors. The rest of the adaptors are white plastic. All of the adaptors have male threads on both sides. The threads on the diverter are female, and the threads in your faucet which your old aerator screwed in to need to be female as well. The metal adaptor fit our old (1970's / 1980's) Moen faucets.

I measured the outside diameter of the threaded part of each of the adaptors - the part that screws into your faucet. Here are the diameters: 0.68-0.69", 0.76-0.77", 0.83-0.84", 0.92" (this is the metal one), and 1.07-1.08". The other side of each of the adaptors (the side that screws into the diverter) measures 0.83-0.84".

I am impressed by the high-quality silicone gaskets that came with the unit. I experienced no leaks.

My faucets are the type where you pull the handle upward to turn it on. This makes it tricky to precisely adjust the water pressure, so the pressure is high enough to wash out food particles, but not so high it is painful to use. I suspect that facets which have handles that you rotate would give easier / more precise control of the water pressure.

title: Seborrheic dermatitis & rosacea sufferer
text: I have suffered with seborrheic dermatitis and rosacea for 15 years and I was excited to stumble upon Face n Earth products as they contain many of the key ingredients which I have read are good for my skin complaints. I have not been disappointed! I have been using the moisturiser for over a month ago with a noticeable improvement ... very minimal breakouts from the dermatitis and not as much redness or visible veins from the Rosacea. I have been using a medicated cream called Elidel, which is a skin inhibitor used for people with eczema-like problems, and for the first time in living memory I am hardly using it at all. Granted, I have been using the Ionic Silver toner in conjunction with the moisturiser but the results have been brilliant! I always read the reviews on Amazon but I think some people are too quick to praise an average product. This is my first online review and it's because it genuinely deserves 5 stars in my opinion ... it's all natural, it smells nice and a little goes a long way. I have been using an Avene cleanser, which is very good, but I am now tempted to purchase all of skin care products from Face n Earth. I have been trying to find all-natural products which aren't unreasonably expensive for a long time and I hope I no longer have to look again. Good work guys!

title: Bad for everyday use, but smells amazing
text:
The first ingredient in this product is Cyclopentasiloxane, which is silicone. While this product has a sweet and subtle scent that is lovely on the hair, habitual silicone use is fundamentally damaging to hair. (Go research Biosilk, a more popular silicone-based hair serum.)

Silicone does create a lovely temporary shine, and it doesn't weigh hair down much. But over time it increases damage, accelerating coarse frizzy hair or split ends. This would make the product addictive: masking the damage CAUSES the damage being covered up.

Who knows, this one may have some effect as claimed in shielding from UV exposure (though I doubt 3-5 drops distributed in a head of damp hair could amount to much sunscreen coverage). And perhaps the Argan oil or other components can balance the effects of the primary silicone ingredient. I wouldn't risk that. I'd use this protector oil for a special occasion for extra pop, shine and an appearance of good grooming, but only with the understanding that occasional use won't cause much harm. It isn't heroin, and using it once won't make you an addict -- just go into it with your eyes open.

Might work for someone who has short, fast-growing hair, where they cut off the hair before damaging effects can become a chronic issue.

title: Robot in disguise?
text:
At first sight, this razor may cause some consternation to Transformers fans, who can't be faulted for thinking that the arcitec 1090 is really the Decepticon known as "Frenzy" in disguise. It stands at attention like a little bathroom sentinel on its silver base, proudly announcing the shaving time on its shiny chest, the three circular razor heads seemingly following your every move while waiting to transform when you least expect it.

Even when it's on the move, it can remain snugly in its futuristic-looking pod, which also has charging capabilities, and looks not unlike a cryogenic holding chamber from sci-fi movies.

From my (and my husband's) experience with this razor, it would be a much better piece of equipment if it actually did something as cool as transform into something else. Unfortunately, it's not much more than a pretty face, and isn't for all types of facial hair (or leg hair for that matter)

Pros:

- Cool looking with a sleek, modern, hi-tech style. Fits very comfortably in your hand.
- There's a display with BIG numbers to indicate how much shaving time you have left. If you ever get caught half way through your shave with no juice, then it's time to see your Optician right away.
- Easy and quick to charge (1 hour). The quick charge feature for a single shave is a nice feature for when you're pressed for time and out of charge.
- Aesthetically pleasing and efficient stand with suction cups to hold it firmly to the counter top. Razor and stand look great next to your expensive bathroom faucets.
- There's a safety lock feature to prevent it from accidentally coming on when travelling. Also useful to prevent your kids from trying to use it.

Cons:
- It gives a reasonably close shave on coarse hair, but you have to keep going over the same spot repeatedly to achieve that. Men's facial hair was okay, but the hair on the neck and chin was almost a mission impossible. (Ladies, forget trying to shave your legs with this razor.) My husband had to resort to a cheaper Norelco model to get those stubborn hairs, and the arcitec left the area under his chin and on his neck feeling irritated and sore.
- It took 12 minutes to shave, almost twice as long as compared to his other razor, even with the larger shaving area.
- The trimmer feature looked useful and functional, but proved to be in a very inconvenient position relative to the shaving heads. You'll need to remove the shaving heads entirely for the trim feature to do its job, and even then, it was not very effective.
- Washing/cleaning after use was easy enough though it meant having to open the three individual cutting heads separately. A simple mechanism to pop all three open simultaneously would have been nice. In addition, the area for catching hair isn't very big.
- The travel pod is a nice bonus feature, but on the big side if space is an issue. You probably don't need the travel pod anyway, since the razor comes with a safety lock.
- Very expensive, and not as efficient as cheaper models.

Norelco did recommend in the manual that you should use it for three weeks without using any other razor so that your skin would adjust to the razor, but at this price, I'm afraid I'll need instant gratification.

Amanda Richards, December 17, 2007

title: Did not work for me
text: Let me begin this review by stating that I have been using Egyptian, Indian and Pakistani 100% henna for over 30 years with beautiful results that lasted a full 3 months.  I decided to try this product because I wanted a change from all the red highlights and thought it would be nice to tone down to a browner hue.  I not only followed the instructions to the letter, but had several exchanges with the seller to make sure what I was doing was correct.  The good news is that this combination beautifully toned down the red from all my prior years of using henna only.  The bad news is that NOT ONE gray hair (I'm dark brown with about 15% gray) gave up being gray! So in addition to the hassle, mess and expense of doing this treatment (and make no mistake - it's messy and time consuming) I will have to double up this month and do my regular henna only routine.  I did a bit of research, by the way, and learned that most henna/indigo distributors, unlike Harvest Moon, suggest mixing up the henna and indigo powders SEPARATELY and then combining.  Based on my experience, I'd have to say this would probably work better (the rationale probably being the same as why combining shampoo and conditioner together don't work as well as shampooing and THEN conditioning).  Likewise, everyone else except Harvest Moon recommends wrapping the hair in plastic wrap and then covering with a shower cap and leaving on for a MINIMUM of 2 hours (Harvest Moon says their product works in less than one hour and is against wrapping.)  Leaves me to wonder if the gray hairs would not be gray had I followed the advice of the other henna/indigo distributors.  Here's a good reference website:  [...]

title: Tastes good, but I haven't noticed a difference in my skin
text:
I've never used a collagen supplement before so I wasn't sure what to expect. I've been using it for a couple weeks now and I can't say I've noticed a marked difference in my skin. Perhaps my skin was already wonderful. :)

I will say for a supplement, this is one of the best tasting ones I've tried. I am always on the look out for new supplements and vitamins, etc. and I really like to try new things to promote skin quality, hair and nail growth, etc. Often the powders or pills or liquids are pretty tough to choke down. I tried a different collagen powder that made me gag so I was kind of worried about trying this.

This is a liquid, but not too viscose. It's thicker than water but easily drinkable and quite tasty. It's a sweet orange flavor. The package says you can add it to smoothies, but I just drink it straight. It does need to stay refrigerated which could be annoying depending on the space available in your refrigerator.

I would probably give it 4 stars for the taste, but the price is so high, and since I haven't noticed a difference I felt I had to knock one more star off. 99 dollars is a lot of money.

title: Very Cute and Practical Baby Shower Gift.
text:
[[VIDEOID:97c749de6240fc65e1ba002f091d004f]] This set of Bandana Drool Bibs for boys by Tiny Captain is too cute. They come packaged in a very nice white cotton draw string bag with cute little baby boy on the front. Inside the bag is a clear plastic bag containing the 4 bibs. The front of each bib is made of 100% cotton and the backing is a very soft 100% polyester. The backing would be very soft on the baby's bare skin if they were not wearing a shirt. I like the fact that the maker took that into consideration, little details like that mean a lot to me. There are two snaps for closure which allows for adjustment as the baby grows. The stitching around the edges is very nice and there weren't corners cut in the bib assembly.

The bibs came in 4 different unique patterns for boys. 2 - Nautical themed bibs one white with sailboats, whales and captain's wheel and the second is a navy blue with white anchors. 1- White with navy, orange and grey air planes. 1 - medium blue with navy bicycles.

I was very satisfied with the quality of bibs I received and I highly recommend these for baby shower gifts, baby gift baskets etc. My daughter used the pointed tips of this type of bib when she was teething to chew on. Because of the shape they catch the drool well and keep from ruining those really cute expensive outfits that we all invest in.

*A sample of this product was provided to me free for testing and review. No promise was made for a positive review.

This is the superior coil hairtie. Seriously. I have a strange hair type, straight but sometimes wavy, fine but dense, and LONG. It's hard finding hair ties that are grippy enough to stay put, but not too tight to cause a headache.

I got into coil hairties this year, and have tried the Inv******ble and Kit** coils. üò¨ They were both underwhelming. Even the ones supposedly for thick hair! They stretched out very easily and unless you stick them in hot water, they don't go back to their original shape.

These are EPIC. Good and firm, way prettier colors and patterns, they stay put, and they return to their original shape much better than others! I'm absolutely a convert!

It wasn't hurting her, I think maybe since it grabbed so much hair, maybe she didn't like the extra little "tug".  There are 2 different curves to the brush and I didn't really notice a difference in the effects.  I also tried to rake the rug, which I have done with my usual brush.  This was absolutely not working with this one.  It grabbed so much it was actually lifting the carpet.  This worked on fine cat hair, so I can only imagine how well it would grab the hair and de-shed a dog.  I didn't have any use for the added light and strap. text:
This stuff is amazing! Every two weeks or so, I spend about 5 minutes doing two rounds of dye on my eyebrows. Brows come out literally perfect every time. I use Roux Clean Touch Haircolor Stain Remover.

No irritation, easy and very fast to apply, and a great color. My eyebrows are naturally almost blonde while my hair is dark brown. This helps even things out and gives me a really natural shade for maybe a dollar per application. There's enough dye in one capsule that I tend to do my brows with TWO of my roommates and we still have a ton to spare. So if you live with other brow-challenged ladies, you can split the cost of one box and share each capsule of dye.

As most of the reviews state, this is a heavy duty metal spray head. HOWEVER, if you think that you can just remove the male quick connect and thread the spray head directly onto your hose, you are WRONG!!! The threads of the hose do not mate with the threads of the spray head. Hopefully, the one I received is defective and this is not a design flaw.

Update.... The seller contacted me to let me know that they shipped the European model, with metric threads, to the USA Amazon distribution center by mistake. They corrected the mistake and now I have a great hose nozzle that threads onto my American hose. Who knew hose threads were not standard around the world.

title: Must have! It really really really really works!
text:
I've had mine for several years now and I could not be more pleased. I'm not going to go into details about all the things everyone else has already said, but I do have a fantastic tip to share.

Lay down on the bed while brushing! Brushing at the sink for 2 or 3 minutes seems like an eternity (especially if you are one of those people who often gets the toothpaste drooling down your chin). Laying down while brushing is one of the best ideas I have ever had. Try this for at least a week and you will be hooked! Relax. Let the toothbrush do the work while you lay down and relax. Enjoy the feeling of the toothbrush massaging your gums and cleaning your teeth. Take your time, and RELAX! (I know, I keep saying relax over and over, but seriously, try taking a little meditation and relaxation break). This makes a mundane chore actually quite enjoyable. If you do this, you will find that you brush longer, and you AND your dentist will notice the results. WARNING! Wait until you get back to the sink to brush your tongue so you don't gag or choke.

By the way, I also have a Sonicare and use it on a regular basis but I prefer this one because it's more controllable.

title: Beard trimmer, Stubble creator
text:
I purchased this product because blades are too expensive these days and I'm just not a morning person. I like the stubble look so after searching product reviews, purchasers of the 980 seemed confident in it's ability to take care of business on setting #1.

It does a great job, 90% of hair gets sucked into the trap. No facial irritation.

The only thing you may need is a regular razor to shape your beard's edges. With the length guard removed you can get pretty close but if you want no hair there you'll need to resort to trimming to zero length then shaping with a razor (while not perfect in that it can't do it all, the results are perfect)!

Pros:
Light
reasonably quiet
no oiling!
grip it by the twist height adjuster and it works great

Cons:
doesn't have a foil-like shaver attachment for removing hair to zero
no stand/dock (only a neg for people who have no place to hide it)
not a smart charger
I believe it's an old style battery so don't expect it to last as long as lithium

text: Peeling foot masks are usually my go-to, but one thing they couldn't seem to solve was the thick calluses on the balls of my feet. I've had them for as long as I can remember, so I began to look for another option. I can't remember what drew my attention to this product or why I decided to go ahead and buy it, but I'm SO glad I did! I could see improvement with just the first use! The instructions say to spray your foot and then scrub with the paddle for 3-5 minutes, but I noticed dead skin coming off in less than a minute. And the cream that comes with it has left my feet smooth and soft. I only wish I could find the foot cream by itself and in a larger container, since I'll definitely run out before I finish the spray. The seller does sell the cream by itself in 2 different sizes for a good price, but the shipping is $30+... not sure what's up with that. The color I have is called Maple Road, a very intense, but subtle brownish red.  It's a matte, and so far has good staying power, and I'm a blotter (only a tiny bit on the tissue).  The box that contains the hard plastic square container tube of lipstick says "Fade Matte Lipstick", but not sure what is meant.  The lipstick itself is the usual swivel type, but with my lipstick when I swiveled it up to use, it didn't want to swivel back down into the protective tube.  I had to gently push the lipstick down into the tube.  Hopefully it's just a glitch with mine.  Anyway, it appears to be a nice lipstick that stays on for a long while, and feels comfortable on the lips

title: Would Recommend!
text:
PROs:
- fast shipping
- variety of designs
- really CHEAP, 2 Konads compared to 21 of same price
- some designs have same quality with Konad plates

CONs:
- some designs are not etched deep enough, like the spider web, i was soo excited for that for Halloween but much to my dismay it wont transfer even with special nail polish. I tried it 10x with different polish, i always end up being disappointed
- very sharp edge
- even after taking the plastic shield off, some plates are still scratched. No biggie..
- the full nail designs are not wide enough. Considering, I have a small nail, but it still wont cover my thumb and middle finger.

TIPS:
- when you take the plastic shield off, use an emery board. Works better than tweezer. Just buff the edge towards the center and peel it off..
- to avoid getting cut with the sharp edge, glue it with a thin cardboard before using. I just use a Cherios box. Lol.
- I didnt use the Konad scraper because plates scratched more easily compared to Konad plates but an old credit card cut in 2, works just fine..

Would I order another one if they have 2nd batch? YES
Would I recommend it to friends? Already Did!

title: Weird wig, but it worked
text: I used this as part of my Peg Bundy costume for Halloween. I had to make some adjustments, but in the end it worked and looked pretty good. First off, the wig cap itself is oddly large in the top. I think this is how it gets the height for the "bump" of the hair. But when wearing it, it's just empty space between the top of the wig cap and the top of your head. And it's not structured at all to help it hold that shape. So I did what any 80's-90's kid would do, and put bump-its on my head, underneath the wig to help fill out that part and give it structure. Also, a headband was necessary to cover up where the bangs meet the rest of the hair, as it was just really weird looking. Then a little teasing and a little aqua net and boom--good to go. I will say also that the wig cap rubbed on my ears uncomfortably, probably compounded by the fact that I had to wear a headband with it. I mean, it's a costume wig, so you get what you get with those, but this was my experience with this purchase.

title: Just my honesty
text:
Honest review:
Okay so I have worn this wig since Saturday and today is Tuesday. My take on the wig since its been washed, knots bleached and flat ironed.

Pros:
Wig didnt smell
Is very full and has body
Knots bleached easier than expected
Lace blends well against skin..may want to use glue rather than hair spray bc it don't hold well.
Wig looks good and dried well after washing.

Cons:
Alot of fly aways, thinner ends in frontal
Construction isnt the best. The wig has a track seperating the frontal from the sewn bundles which is irritating because the part isnt that long which leaves me with the only option; remove it or monitor whether its showing or not which is uncomfortable bc a wig shouldnt expose you. This irritates me BIG !!!!
The frontal of the wig is whispy and not as full as the back. Im not sure if its the humidity outside or not but I flatironed it this morning and it looks more of a body wave in the front and straight in the back. Most bobs dont look like that, so this was is a must for me.
Wig cap is HUGE. If tou have an average sized small head you will have to customize this unit. I do understand that they make them to where they can be adjusted to the customers liking abd or big head friendly bc everyones head comes in different sizes but I struggled today lol. I reconstructed the whole wig in the back. I took four tracks out the back and cut the comb out and replaced it to help on the track line and sewed it through the cap for the much needed support. I had to cut the sides down as well bc it was really bulky. I sewed the band that came with the wig into the wig as well to hold the bulkeness down more. When I say I was tired I was but all in all I like it better now, my head is just small. Hopefully I can figure this seperatung track out. I may just use this wig when I want to pull the hair up or something bc I cant be worried about this. üò¨ Im not sure of anyone else experienced this with their purchase, but it may have been just mine. I will update once it get colder as far as the hair spray sticking good and the the whispyness of the sides that cant seem to stay straigh all day.

On the 3rd tray I had some sensitivity & preservered thru it as recommended for optimal whitening. No sensitivity noted with all following treatments. A month later, I found this on Amazon ($69.99 with toothpaste!!) and purchased. Had some sensitivity where it did burn my gum line (gums turned white after whitening treatment) from biting down too hard and getting some excess whitening agent on my gum line. Tried to keep going but stopped bc it hurt really bad and different from the pain from just tooth sensitivity. I let it heal & continued a few days later. Concerned it was due to just being an Amazon product and not the same as what I bought at the dental office, I bit the bullet & purchased another from the dental office and compared everything: boxes (same), expiration dates (legit), trays (same design). When I buy again, I will definitely save myself $20 & go on Amazon & get some free toothpaste. My teeth are noticeably whiter. And whitened 1.5 shades in a box's worth. Definitely recommend.

title: My New Favorite lipstick
text: I AM IN LOVE WITH THIS LIPSTICK!!!! This was my first time trying 'Love Brights gel matte lipstick' and I am hooked! I've never known any lipstick to smell so good when applied! I could compare the scent to a chery lip gloss. I didn't get that sticky residual or bitter taste some lipsticks leave behind. Love Brights lipstick is enriched with Evening Primrose and Cherry Oils which adds moisture naturally to your lips and my lips were definitely moisturized after I applied it. I usually have to add a lip gloss on top of my lipstick to add a little shine but i didnt need to do that with Love Brighs lipstick either. I was given the opportunity to try this product at a discounted price in exchange for an unbiased and honest review.
